#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:256
msgid ""
"`#13737 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13737>`_: Added the :"
"confval:`strict_parametrization_ids` configuration option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:258
msgid ""
"When set, pytest emits an error if it detects non-unique parameter set IDs, "
"rather than automatically making the IDs unique by adding `0`, `1`, ... to "
"them. This can be particularly useful for catching unintended duplicates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:263
msgid ""
"`#13072 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13072>`_: Added support "
"for displaying test session **progress in the terminal tab** using the `OSC "
"9;4; <https://conemu.github.io/en/AnsiEscapeCodes."
"html#ConEmu_specific_OSC>`_ ANSI sequence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:265
msgid ""
"**Note**: *This feature has been disabled by default in version 9.0.2, "
"except on Windows, due to compatibility issues with some terminal emulators. "
"You may enable it again by passing* ``-p terminalprogress``. *We may enable "
"it by default again once compatibility improves in the future.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:268
msgid ""
"When pytest runs in a supported terminal emulator like ConEmu, Gnome "
"Terminal, Ptyxis, Windows Terminal, Kitty or Ghostty, you'll see the "
"progress in the terminal tab or window, allowing you to monitor pytest's "
"progress at a glance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:272
msgid ""
"This feature is automatically enabled when running in a TTY. It is "
"implemented as an internal plugin. If needed, it can be disabled as follows: "
"- On a user level, using ``-p no:terminalprogress`` on the command line or "
"via an environment variable ``PYTEST_ADDOPTS='-p no:terminalprogress'``. - "
"On a project configuration level, using ``addopts = \"-p no:"
"terminalprogress\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:277
msgid ""
"`#478 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/478>`_: Support PEP420 "
"(implicit namespace packages) as `--pyargs` target when :confval:"
"`consider_namespace_packages` is `true` in the config."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:279
msgid ""
"Previously, this option only impacted package imports, now it also impacts "
"tests discovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:282
msgid ""
"`#13678 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13678>`_: Added a new :"
"confval:`faulthandler_exit_on_timeout` configuration option set to \"false\" "
"by default to let `faulthandler` interrupt the `pytest` process after a "
"timeout in case of deadlock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:284
msgid ""
"Previously, a `faulthandler` timeout would only dump the traceback of all "
"threads to stderr, but would not interrupt the `pytest` process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:286
msgid "-- by :user:`ogrisel`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:289
msgid ""
"`#13829 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13829>`_: Added support "
"for configuration option aliases via the ``aliases`` parameter in :meth:"
"`Parser.addini() <pytest.Parser.addini>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:291
msgid ""
"Plugins can now register alternative names for configuration options, "
"allowing for more flexibility in configuration naming and supporting "
"backward compatibility when renaming options. The canonical name always "
"takes precedence if both the canonical name and an alias are specified in "
"the configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:300
msgid ""
"`#13330 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13330>`_: Having pytest "
"configuration spread over more than one file (for example having both a "
"``pytest.ini`` file and ``pyproject.toml`` with a ``[tool.pytest."
"ini_options]`` table) will now print a warning to make it clearer to the "
"user that only one of them is actually used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:302
msgid "-- by :user:`sgaist`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:305
msgid ""
"`#13574 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13574>`_: The single "
"argument ``--version`` no longer loads the entire plugin infrastructure, "
"making it faster and more reliable when displaying only the pytest version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:307
msgid ""
"Passing ``--version`` twice (e.g., ``pytest --version --version``) retains "
"the original behavior, showing both the pytest version and plugin "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:311
msgid ""
"Since ``--version`` is now processed early, it only takes effect when passed "
"directly via the command line. It will not work if set through other "
"mechanisms, such as :envvar:`PYTEST_ADDOPTS` or :confval:`addopts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:314
msgid ""
"`#13823 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13823>`_: Added :"
"confval:`strict_xfail` as an alias to the ``xfail_strict`` option, :confval:"
"`strict_config` as an alias to the ``--strict-config`` flag, and :confval:"
"`strict_markers` as an alias to the ``--strict-markers`` flag. This makes "
"all strictness options consistently have configuration options with the "
"prefix ``strict_``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:319
msgid ""
"`#13700 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13700>`_: `--junitxml`  "
"no longer prints the `generated xml file` summary at the end of the pytest "
"session when `--quiet` is given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:322
msgid ""
"`#13732 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13732>`_: Previously, "
"when filtering warnings, pytest would fail if the filter referenced a class "
"that could not be imported. Now, this only outputs a message indicating the "
"problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:325
msgid ""
"`#13859 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13859>`_: Clarify the "
"error message for `pytest.raises()` when a regex `match` fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:328
msgid ""
"`#13861 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13861>`_: Better "
"sentence structure in a test's expected error message. Previously, the error "
"message would be \"expected exception must be <expected>, but got "
"<actual>\". Now, it is \"Expected <expected>, but got <actual>\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:332 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:543
msgid "Removals and backward incompatible breaking changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:334
msgid ""
"`#12083 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12083>`_: Fixed a bug "
"where an invocation such as `pytest a/ a/b` would cause only tests from `a/"
"b` to run, and not other tests under `a/`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:336
msgid ""
"The fix entails a few breaking changes to how such overlapping arguments and "
"duplicates are handled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:338
msgid ""
"`pytest a/b a/` or `pytest a/ a/b` are equivalent to `pytest a`; if an "
"argument overlaps another arguments, only the prefix remains."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:340
msgid ""
"`pytest x.py x.py` is equivalent to `pytest x.py`; previously such an "
"invocation was taken as an explicit request to run the tests from the file "
"twice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:342
msgid ""
"If you rely on these behaviors, consider using :ref:`--keep-duplicates "
"<duplicate-paths>`, which retains its existing behavior (including the bug)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:345
msgid ""
"`#13719 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13719>`_: Support for "
"Python 3.9 is dropped following its end of life."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:348
msgid ""
"`#13766 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13766>`_: Previously, "
"pytest would assume it was running in a CI/CD environment if either of the "
"environment variables `$CI` or `$BUILD_NUMBER` was defined; now, CI mode is "
"only activated if at least one of those variables is defined and set to a "
"*non-empty* value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:352
msgid ""
"The non-public ``config.args`` attribute used to be able to contain "
"``pathlib.Path`` instances; now it can only contain strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:355
msgid ""
"`#13779 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13779>`_: "
"**PytestRemovedIn9Warning deprecation warnings are now errors by default.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:357
msgid ""
"Following our plan to remove deprecated features with as little disruption "
"as possible, all warnings of type ``PytestRemovedIn9Warning`` now generate "
"errors instead of warning messages by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:361
msgid ""
"**The affected features will be effectively removed in pytest 9.1**, so "
"please consult the :ref:`deprecations` section in the docs for directions on "
"how to update existing code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:364
msgid ""
"In the pytest ``9.0.X`` series, it is possible to change the errors back "
"into warnings as a stopgap measure by adding this to your ``pytest.ini`` "
"file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:367
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"filterwarnings =\n"
"    ignore::pytest.PytestRemovedIn9Warning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:373
msgid "But this will stop working when pytest ``9.1`` is released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:375
msgid ""
"**If you have concerns** about the removal of a specific feature, please add "
"a comment to :issue:`13779`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:383
msgid ""
"`#13807 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13807>`_: :meth:"
"`monkeypatch.syspath_prepend() <pytest.MonkeyPatch.syspath_prepend>` now "
"issues a deprecation warning when the prepended path contains legacy "
"namespace packages (those using ``pkg_resources.declare_namespace()``). "
"Users should migrate to native namespace packages (:pep:`420`). See :ref:"
"`monkeypatch-fixup-namespace-packages` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:391
msgid ""
"`#13445 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13445>`_: Made the type "
"annotations of :func:`pytest.skip` and friends more spec-complaint to have "
"them work across more type checkers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:394
msgid ""
"`#13537 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13537>`_: Fixed a bug "
"in which :class:`ExceptionGroup` with only ``Skipped`` exceptions in "
"teardown was not handled correctly and showed as error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:397
msgid ""
"`#13598 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13598>`_: Fixed "
"possible collection confusion on Windows when short paths and symlinks are "
"involved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:400
msgid ""
"`#13716 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13716>`_: Fixed a bug "
"where a nonsensical invocation like ``pytest x.py[a]`` (a file cannot be "
"parametrized) was silently treated as ``pytest x.py``. This is now a usage "
"error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:403
msgid ""
"`#13722 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13722>`_: Fixed a "
"misleading assertion failure message when using :func:`pytest.approx` on "
"mappings with differing lengths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:406
msgid ""
"`#13773 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13773>`_: Fixed the "
"static fixture closure calculation to properly consider transitive "
"dependencies requested by overridden fixtures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:409
msgid ""
"`#13816 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13816>`_: Fixed :func:"
"`pytest.approx` which now returns a clearer error message when comparing "
"mappings with different keys."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:412
msgid ""
"`#13849 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13849>`_: Hidden ``."
"pytest.ini`` files are now picked up as the config file even if empty. This "
"was an inconsistency with non-hidden ``pytest.ini``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:416
msgid ""
"`#13865 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13865>`_: Fixed `--show-"
"capture` with `--tb=line`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:419
msgid ""
"`#13522 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13522>`_: Fixed :"
"fixture:`pytester` in subprocess mode ignored all :attr:`pytester.plugins "
"<pytest.Pytester.plugins>` except the first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:421
msgid ""
"Fixed :fixture:`pytester` in subprocess mode silently ignored non-str :attr:"
"`pytester.plugins <pytest.Pytester.plugins>`. Now it errors instead. If you "
"are affected by this, specify the plugin by name, or switch the affected "
"tests to use :func:`pytester.runpytest_inprocess <pytest.Pytester."
"runpytest_inprocess>` explicitly instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:430
msgid ""
"`#13791 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13791>`_: Minimum "
"requirements on ``iniconfig`` and ``packaging`` were bumped to ``1.0.1`` and "
"``22.0.0``, respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:437
msgid ""
"`#12244 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12244>`_: Fixed self-"
"test failures when `TERM=dumb`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:440
msgid ""
"`#12474 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12474>`_: Added "
"scheduled GitHub Action Workflow to run Sphinx linkchecks in repo "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:443
msgid ""
"`#13621 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13621>`_: pytest's own "
"testsuite now handles the ``lsof`` command hanging (e.g. due to unreachable "
"network filesystems), with the affected selftests being skipped after 10 "
"seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:446
msgid ""
"`#13638 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13638>`_: Fixed "
"deprecated :command:`gh pr new` command in :file:`scripts/prepare-release-pr."
"py`. The script now uses :command:`gh pr create` which is compatible with "
"GitHub CLI v2.0+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:450
msgid ""
"`#13695 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13695>`_: Flush "
"`stdout` and `stderr` in `Pytester.run` to avoid truncated outputs in "
"`test_faulthandler.py::test_timeout` on CI -- by :user:`ogrisel`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:453
msgid ""
"`#13771 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13771>`_: Skip "
"`test_do_not_collect_symlink_siblings` on Windows environments without "
"symlink support to avoid false negatives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:456
msgid ""
"`#13841 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13841>`_: ``tox>=4`` is "
"now required when contributing to pytest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:458
msgid ""
"`#13625 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13625>`_: Added missing "
"docstrings to ``pytest_addoption()``, ``pytest_configure()``, and "
"``cacheshow()`` functions in ``cacheprovider.py``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:463 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:955
#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1083
msgid "Miscellaneous internal changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:465
msgid ""
"`#13830 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13830>`_: Configuration "
"overrides (``-o``/``--override-ini``) are now processed during startup "
"rather than during :func:`config.getini() <pytest.Config.getini>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:469
msgid "pytest 8.4.2 (2025-09-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:474
msgid ""
"`#13478 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13478>`_: Fixed a crash "
"when using :confval:`console_output_style` with ``times`` and a module is "
"skipped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:477
msgid ""
"`#13530 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13530>`_: Fixed a crash "
"when using :func:`pytest.approx` and :class:`decimal.Decimal` instances with "
"the :class:`decimal.FloatOperation` trap set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:480
msgid ""
"`#13549 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13549>`_: No longer "
"evaluate type annotations in Python ``3.14`` when inspecting function "
"signatures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:482
msgid ""
"This prevents crashes during module collection when modules do not "
"explicitly use ``from __future__ import annotations`` and import types for "
"annotations within a ``if TYPE_CHECKING:`` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:485
msgid ""
"`#13559 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13559>`_: Added missing "
"`int` and `float` variants to the `Literal` type annotation of the `type` "
"parameter in :meth:`pytest.Parser.addini`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:488
msgid ""
"`#13563 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13563>`_: :func:`pytest."
"approx` now only imports ``numpy`` if NumPy is already in ``sys.modules``. "
"This fixes unconditional import behavior introduced in `8.4.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:495
msgid ""
"`#13577 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13577>`_: Clarify that "
"``pytest_generate_tests`` is discovered in test modules/classes; other hooks "
"must be in ``conftest.py`` or plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:502
msgid ""
"`#13480 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13480>`_: Self-testing: "
"fixed a few test failures when run with ``-Wdefault`` or a similar override."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:505
msgid ""
"`#13547 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13547>`_: Self-testing: "
"corrected expected message for ``test_doctest_unexpected_exception`` in "
"Python ``3.14``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:508
msgid ""
"`#13684 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13684>`_: Make pytest's "
"own testsuite insensitive to the presence of the ``CI`` environment variable "
"-- by :user:`ogrisel`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:512
msgid "pytest 8.4.1 (2025-06-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:517
msgid ""
"`#13461 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13461>`_: Corrected "
"``_pytest.terminal.TerminalReporter.isatty`` to support being called as a "
"method. Before it was just a boolean which could break correct code when "
"using ``-o log_cli=true``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:522
msgid ""
"`#13477 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13477>`_: Reintroduced :"
"class:`pytest.PytestReturnNotNoneWarning` which was removed by accident in "
"pytest `8.4`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:524
msgid ""
"This warning is raised when a test functions returns a value other than "
"``None``, which is often a mistake made by beginners."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:526
msgid "See :ref:`return-not-none` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:529
msgid ""
"`#13497 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13497>`_: Fixed "
"compatibility with ``Twisted 25+``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:536
msgid ""
"`#13492 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13492>`_: Fixed "
"outdated warning about ``faulthandler`` not working on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:540
msgid "pytest 8.4.0 (2025-06-02)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:545
msgid ""
"`#11372 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11372>`_: Async tests "
"will now fail, instead of warning+skipping, if you don't have any suitable "
"plugin installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:548
msgid ""
"`#12346 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12346>`_: Tests will "
"now fail, instead of raising a warning, if they return any value other than "
"None."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:551
msgid ""
"`#12874 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12874>`_: We dropped "
"support for Python 3.8 following its end of life (2024-10-07)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:554
msgid ""
"`#12960 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12960>`_: Test "
"functions containing a yield now cause an explicit error. They have not been "
"run since pytest 4.0, and were previously marked as an expected failure and "
"deprecation warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:556
msgid "See :ref:`the docs <yield tests deprecated>` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:563
msgid ""
"`#10839 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/10839>`_: Requesting an "
"asynchronous fixture without a `pytest_fixture_setup` hook that resolves it "
"will now give a DeprecationWarning. This most commonly happens if a sync "
"test requests an async fixture. This should have no effect on a majority of "
"users with async tests or fixtures using async pytest plugins, but may "
"affect non-standard hook setups or ``autouse=True``. For guidance on how to "
"work around this warning see :ref:`sync-test-async-fixture`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:570
msgid ""
"`#11538 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11538>`_: Added :class:"
"`pytest.RaisesGroup` as an equivalent to :func:`pytest.raises` for "
"expecting :exc:`ExceptionGroup`. Also adds :class:`pytest.RaisesExc` which "
"is now the logic behind :func:`pytest.raises` and used as parameter to :"
"class:`pytest.RaisesGroup`. ``RaisesGroup`` includes the ability to specify "
"multiple different expected exceptions, the structure of nested exception "
"groups, and flags for emulating :ref:`except* <except_star>`. See :ref:"
"`assert-matching-exception-groups` and docstrings for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:573
msgid ""
"`#12081 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12081>`_: Added :"
"fixture:`capteesys` to capture AND pass output to next handler set by ``--"
"capture=``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:576
msgid ""
"`#12504 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12504>`_: :func:`pytest."
"mark.xfail` now accepts :class:`pytest.RaisesGroup` for the ``raises`` "
"parameter when you expect an exception group. You can also pass a :class:"
"`pytest.RaisesExc` if you e.g. want to make use of the ``check`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:579
msgid ""
"`#12713 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12713>`_: New `--force-"
"short-summary` option to force condensed summary output regardless of "
"verbosity level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:581
msgid ""
"This lets users still see condensed summary output of failures for quick "
"reference in log files from job outputs, being especially useful if non-"
"condensed output is very verbose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:584
msgid ""
"`#12749 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12749>`_: pytest "
"traditionally collects classes/functions in the test module namespace even "
"if they are imported from another file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:586
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:588
msgid ""
"# contents of src/domain.py\n"
"class Testament: ...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"# contents of tests/test_testament.py\n"
"from domain import Testament\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test_testament(): ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:600
msgid ""
"In this scenario with the default options, pytest will collect the class "
"`Testament` from `tests/test_testament.py` because it starts with `Test`, "
"even though in this case it is a production class being imported in the test "
"module namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:602
msgid ""
"This behavior can now be prevented by setting the new :confval:"
"`collect_imported_tests` configuration option to ``false``, which will make "
"pytest collect classes/functions from test files **only** if they are "
"defined in that file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:604
msgid "-- by :user:`FreerGit`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:607
msgid ""
"`#12765 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12765>`_: Thresholds to "
"trigger snippet truncation can now be set with :confval:"
"`truncation_limit_lines` and :confval:`truncation_limit_chars`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:609
msgid "See :ref:`truncation-params` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:612
msgid ""
"`#13125 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13125>`_: :confval:"
"`console_output_style` now supports ``times`` to show execution time of each "
"test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:615
msgid ""
"`#13192 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13192>`_: :func:`pytest."
"raises` will now raise a warning when passing an empty string to ``match``, "
"as this will match against any value. Use ``match=\"^$\"`` if you want to "
"check that an exception has no message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:618
msgid ""
"`#13192 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13192>`_: :func:`pytest."
"raises` will now print a helpful string diff if matching fails and the match "
"parameter has ``^`` and ``$`` and is otherwise escaped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:621
msgid ""
"`#13192 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13192>`_: You can now "
"pass :func:`with pytest.raises(check=fn): <pytest.raises>`, where ``fn`` is "
"a function which takes a raised exception and returns a boolean. The "
"``raises`` fails if no exception was raised (as usual), passes if an "
"exception is raised and ``fn`` returns ``True`` (as well as ``match`` and "
"the type matching, if specified, which are checked before), and propagates "
"the exception if ``fn`` returns ``False`` (which likely also fails the test)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:624
msgid ""
"`#13228 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13228>`_: :ref:`hidden-"
"param` can now be used in ``id`` of :func:`pytest.param` or in ``ids`` of :"
"py:func:`Metafunc.parametrize <pytest.Metafunc.parametrize>`. It hides the "
"parameter set from the test name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:629
msgid ""
"`#13253 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13253>`_: New flag: :"
"ref:`--disable-plugin-autoload <disable_plugin_autoload>` which works as an "
"alternative to :envvar:`PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD` when setting "
"environment variables is inconvenient; and allows setting it in config files "
"with :confval:`addopts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:636
msgid ""
"`#10224 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/10224>`_: pytest's "
"``short`` and ``long`` traceback styles (:ref:`how-to-modifying-python-tb-"
"printing`) now have partial :pep:`657` support and will show specific code "
"segments in the traceback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:640
msgid ""
"================================= FAILURES "
"=================================\n"
"_______________________ test_gets_correct_tracebacks "
"_______________________\n"
"\n"
"test_tracebacks.py:12: in test_gets_correct_tracebacks\n"
"    assert manhattan_distance(p1, p2) == 1\n"
"           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n"
"test_tracebacks.py:6: in manhattan_distance\n"
"    return abs(point_1.x - point_2.x) + abs(point_1.y - point_2.y)\n"
"                           ^^^^^^^^^\n"
"E   AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'x'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:653
msgid "-- by :user:`ammaraskar`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:656
msgid ""
"`#11118 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11118>`_: Now :confval:"
"`pythonpath` configures `$PYTHONPATH` earlier than before during the "
"initialization process, which now also affects plugins loaded via the `-p` "
"command-line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:658
msgid "-- by :user:`millerdev`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:661
msgid ""
"`#11381 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11381>`_: The ``type`` "
"parameter of the ``parser.addini`` method now accepts `\"int\"` and "
"``\"float\"`` parameters, facilitating the parsing of configuration values "
"in the configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:665
msgid ""
"def pytest_addoption(parser):\n"
"    parser.addini(\"int_value\", type=\"int\", default=2, help=\"my int "
"value\")\n"
"    parser.addini(\"float_value\", type=\"float\", default=4.2, help=\"my "
"float value\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:671
msgid "The `pytest.ini` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:673
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"int_value = 3\n"
"float_value = 5.4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:680
msgid ""
"`#11525 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11525>`_: Fixtures are "
"now clearly represented in the output as a \"fixture object\", not as a "
"normal function as before, making it easy for beginners to catch mistakes "
"such as referencing a fixture declared in the same module but not requested "
"in the test function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:682
msgid "-- by :user:`the-compiler` and :user:`glyphack`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:685
msgid ""
"`#12426 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12426>`_: A warning is "
"now issued when :ref:`pytest.mark.usefixtures ref` is used without "
"specifying any fixtures. Previously, empty usefixtures markers were silently "
"ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:688
msgid ""
"`#12707 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12707>`_: Exception "
"chains can be navigated when dropped into Pdb in Python 3.13+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:691
msgid ""
"`#12736 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12736>`_: Added a new "
"attribute `name` with the fixed value `\"pytest tests\"` to the root tag "
"`testsuites` of the junit-xml generated by pytest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:693
msgid ""
"This attribute is part of many junit-xml specifications and is even part of "
"the `junit-10.xsd` specification that pytest's implementation is based on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:696
msgid ""
"`#12943 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12943>`_: If a test "
"fails with an exceptiongroup with a single exception, the contained "
"exception will now be displayed in the short test summary info."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:699
msgid ""
"`#12958 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12958>`_: A number of :"
"ref:`unraisable <unraisable>` enhancements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:701
msgid ""
"Set the unraisable hook as early as possible and unset it as late as "
"possible, to collect the most possible number of unraisable exceptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:702
msgid ""
"Call the garbage collector just before unsetting the unraisable hook, to "
"collect any straggling exceptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:703
msgid "Collect multiple unraisable exceptions per test phase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:704 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:717
msgid "Report the :mod:`tracemalloc` allocation traceback (if available)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:705 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:718
msgid ""
"Avoid using a generator based hook to allow handling :class:`StopIteration` "
"in test failures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:706
msgid ""
"Report the unraisable exception as the cause of the :class:`pytest."
"PytestUnraisableExceptionWarning` exception if raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:707
msgid ""
"Compute the ``repr`` of the unraisable object in the unraisable hook so you "
"get the latest information if available, and should help with resurrection "
"of the object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:710
msgid ""
"`#13010 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13010>`_: :func:`pytest."
"approx` now can compare collections that contain numbers and non-numbers "
"mixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:713
msgid ""
"`#13016 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13016>`_: A number of :"
"ref:`threadexception <unraisable>` enhancements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:715
msgid ""
"Set the excepthook as early as possible and unset it as late as possible, to "
"collect the most possible number of unhandled exceptions from threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:716
msgid "Collect multiple thread exceptions per test phase."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:719
msgid ""
"Report the thread exception as the cause of the :class:`pytest."
"PytestUnhandledThreadExceptionWarning` exception if raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:720
msgid ""
"Extract the ``name`` of the thread object in the excepthook which should "
"help with resurrection of the thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:723
msgid ""
"`#13031 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13031>`_: An empty "
"parameter set as in ``pytest.mark.parametrize([], ids=idfunc)`` will no "
"longer trigger a call to ``idfunc`` with internal objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:726
msgid ""
"`#13115 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13115>`_: Allows "
"supplying ``ExceptionGroup[Exception]`` and "
"``BaseExceptionGroup[BaseException]`` to ``pytest.raises`` to keep full "
"typing on :class:`ExceptionInfo <pytest.ExceptionInfo>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:728
msgid ""
"with pytest.raises(ExceptionGroup[Exception]) as exc_info:\n"
"    some_function()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:733
msgid ""
"Parametrizing with other exception types remains an error - we do not check "
"the types of child exceptions and thus do not permit code that might look "
"like we do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:736
msgid ""
"`#13122 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13122>`_: The ``--"
"stepwise`` mode received a number of improvements:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:738
msgid ""
"It no longer forgets the last failed test in case pytest is executed later "
"without the flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:740
msgid "This enables the following workflow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:742
msgid ""
"Execute pytest with ``--stepwise``, pytest then stops at the first failing "
"test;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:743
msgid ""
"Iteratively update the code and run the test in isolation, without the ``--"
"stepwise`` flag (for example in an IDE), until it is fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:744
msgid ""
"Execute pytest with ``--stepwise`` again and pytest will continue from the "
"previously failed test, and if it passes, continue on to the next tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:746
msgid ""
"Previously, at step 3, pytest would start from the beginning, forgetting the "
"previously failed test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:748
msgid ""
"This change however might cause issues if the ``--stepwise`` mode is used "
"far apart in time, as the state might get stale, so the internal state will "
"be reset automatically in case the test suite changes (for now only the "
"number of tests are considered for this, we might change/improve this on the "
"future)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:750
msgid ""
"New ``--stepwise-reset``/``--sw-reset`` flag, allowing the user to "
"explicitly reset the stepwise state and restart the workflow from the "
"beginning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:753
msgid ""
"`#13308 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13308>`_: Added "
"official support for Python 3.14."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:756
msgid ""
"`#13380 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13380>`_: Fix :class:"
"`ExceptionGroup` traceback filtering to exclude pytest internals."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:759
msgid ""
"`#13415 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13415>`_: The author "
"metadata of the BibTex example is now correctly formatted with last names "
"following first names. An example of BibLaTex has been added. BibTex and "
"BibLaTex examples now clearly indicate that what is cited is software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:763
msgid "-- by :user:`willynilly`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:766
msgid ""
"`#13420 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13420>`_: Improved test "
"collection performance by optimizing path resolution used in ``FSCollector``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:769
msgid ""
"`#13457 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13457>`_: The error "
"message about duplicate parametrization no longer displays an internal stack "
"trace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:772
msgid ""
"`#4112 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4112>`_: Using :ref:"
"`pytest.mark.usefixtures <pytest.mark.usefixtures ref>` on :func:`pytest."
"param` now produces an error instead of silently doing nothing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:775
msgid ""
"`#5473 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5473>`_: Replace `:` "
"with `;` in the assertion rewrite warning message so it can be filtered "
"using standard Python warning filters before calling :func:`pytest.main`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:778
msgid ""
"`#6985 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/6985>`_: Improved :func:"
"`pytest.approx` to enhance the readability of value ranges and tolerances "
"between 0.001 and 1000."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:779
msgid ""
"The `repr` method now provides clearer output for values within those "
"ranges, making it easier to interpret the results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:780
msgid ""
"Previously, the output for those ranges of values and tolerances was "
"displayed in scientific notation (e.g., `42 ± 1.0e+00`). The updated method "
"now presents the tolerance as a decimal for better readability (e.g., `42 ± "
"1`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:784
msgid "**Previous Output:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:786
msgid ""
">>> pytest.approx(42, abs=1)\n"
"42 ± 1.0e+00"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:791
msgid "**Current Output:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:793
msgid ""
">>> pytest.approx(42, abs=1)\n"
"42 ± 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:798
msgid "-- by :user:`fazeelghafoor`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:801
msgid ""
"`#7683 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7683>`_: The formerly "
"optional ``pygments`` dependency is now required, causing output always to "
"be source-highlighted (unless disabled via the ``--code-highlight=no`` CLI "
"option)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:808
msgid ""
"`#10404 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/10404>`_: Apply "
"filterwarnings from config/cli as soon as possible, and revert them as late "
"as possible so that warnings as errors are collected throughout the pytest "
"run and before the unraisable and threadexcept hooks are removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:812
msgid ""
"This allows very late warnings and unraisable/threadexcept exceptions to "
"fail the test suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:814
msgid ""
"This also changes the warning that the lsof plugin issues from PytestWarning "
"to the new warning PytestFDWarning so it can be more easily filtered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:817
msgid ""
"`#11067 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/11067>`_: The test "
"report is now consistent regardless if the test xfailed via :ref:`pytest."
"mark.xfail <pytest.mark.xfail ref>` or :func:`pytest.fail`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:819
msgid ""
"Previously, *xfailed* tests via the marker would have the string ``\"reason: "
"\"`` prefixed to the message, while those *xfailed* via the function did "
"not. The prefix has been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:822
msgid ""
"`#12008 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12008>`_: In :pr:"
"`11220`, an unintended change in reordering was introduced by changing the "
"way indices were assigned to direct params. More specifically, before that "
"change, the indices of direct params to metafunc's callspecs were assigned "
"after all parametrizations took place. Now, that change is reverted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:825
msgid ""
"`#12863 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12863>`_: Fix applying "
"markers, including :ref:`pytest.mark.parametrize <pytest.mark.parametrize "
"ref>` when placed above `@staticmethod` or `@classmethod`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:828
msgid ""
"`#12929 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12929>`_: Handle "
"StopIteration from test cases, setup and teardown correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:831
msgid ""
"`#12938 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12938>`_: Fixed ``--"
"durations-min`` argument not respected if ``-vv`` is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:834
msgid ""
"`#12946 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12946>`_: Fixed missing "
"help for :mod:`pdb` commands wrapped by pytest -- by :user:`adamchainz`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:837
msgid ""
"`#12981 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12981>`_: Prevent "
"exceptions in :func:`pytest.Config.add_cleanup` callbacks preventing further "
"cleanups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:840
msgid ""
"`#13047 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13047>`_: Restore :func:"
"`pytest.approx` handling of equality checks between `bool` and `numpy.bool_` "
"types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:842
msgid ""
"Comparing `bool` and `numpy.bool_` using :func:`pytest.approx` accidentally "
"changed in version `8.3.4` and `8.3.5` to no longer match:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:844
msgid ""
">>> import numpy as np\n"
">>> from pytest import approx\n"
">>> [np.True_, np.True_] == pytest.approx([True, True])\n"
"False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:851
msgid "This has now been fixed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:853
msgid ""
">>> [np.True_, np.True_] == pytest.approx([True, True])\n"
"True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:859
msgid ""
"`#13119 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13119>`_: Improved "
"handling of invalid regex patterns for filter warnings by providing a clear "
"error message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:862
msgid ""
"`#13175 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13175>`_: The diff is "
"now also highlighted correctly when comparing two strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:865
msgid ""
"`#13248 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13248>`_: Fixed an "
"issue where passing a ``scope`` in :py:func:`Metafunc.parametrize <pytest."
"Metafunc.parametrize>` with ``indirect=True`` could result in other fixtures "
"being unable to depend on the parametrized fixture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:869
msgid ""
"`#13291 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13291>`_: Fixed "
"``repr`` of ``attrs`` objects in assertion failure messages when using "
"``attrs>=25.2``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:872
msgid ""
"`#13312 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13312>`_: Fixed a "
"possible ``KeyError`` crash on PyPy during collection of tests involving "
"higher-scoped parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:875
msgid ""
"`#13345 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13345>`_: Fix type "
"hints for :attr:`pytest.TestReport.when` and :attr:`pytest.TestReport."
"location`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:878
msgid ""
"`#13377 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13377>`_: Fixed "
"handling of test methods with positional-only parameter syntax."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:880
msgid ""
"Now, methods are supported that formally define ``self`` as positional-only "
"and/or fixture parameters as keyword-only, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:883
msgid ""
"class TestClass:\n"
"\n"
"    def test_method(self, /, *, fixture): ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:889
msgid "Before, this caused an internal error in pytest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:892
msgid ""
"`#13384 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13384>`_: Fixed an "
"issue where pytest could report negative durations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:895
msgid ""
"`#13420 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13420>`_: Added "
"``lru_cache`` to ``nodes._check_initialpaths_for_relpath``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:898
msgid ""
"`#9037 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9037>`_: Honor :confval:"
"`disable_test_id_escaping_and_forfeit_all_rights_to_community_support` when "
"escaping ids in parametrized tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:905
msgid ""
"`#12535 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12535>`_: `This "
"example`<https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/example/simple.html#making-test-"
"result-information-available-in-fixtures> showed ``print`` statements that "
"do not exactly reflect what the different branches actually do.  The fix "
"makes the example more precise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:911
msgid ""
"`#13218 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/13218>`_: Pointed out "
"in the :func:`pytest.approx` documentation that it considers booleans "
"unequal to numeric zero or one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:914
msgid ""
