msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1250
msgid ""
"`#6962 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/6962>`_: Parametrization "
"parameters are now compared using `==` instead of `is` (`is` is still used "
"as a fallback if the parameter does not support `==`). This fixes use of "
"parameters such as lists, which have a different `id` but compare equal, "
"causing fixtures to be re-computed instead of being cached."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1254
msgid ""
"`#7166 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7166>`_: Fixed progress "
"percentages (the ``[ 87%]`` at the edge of the screen) sometimes not "
"aligning correctly when running with pytest-xdist ``-n``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1261
msgid ""
"`#12153 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12153>`_: Documented "
"using :envvar:`PYTEST_VERSION` to detect if code is running from within a "
"pytest run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1264
msgid ""
"`#12469 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12469>`_: The external "
"plugin mentions in the documentation now avoid mentioning :std:doc:"
"`setuptools entry-points <setuptools:index>` as the concept is much more "
