#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1308
msgid ""
"`#12498 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12498>`_: All the "
"undocumented ``tox`` environments now have descriptions. They can be listed "
"in one's development environment by invoking ``tox -av`` in a terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1315
msgid ""
"`#12501 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12501>`_: The changelog "
"configuration has been updated to introduce more accurate audience-tailored "
"categories. Previously, there was a ``trivial`` change log fragment type "
"with an unclear and broad meaning. It was removed and we now have "
"``contrib``, ``misc`` and ``packaging`` in place of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1321
msgid ""
"The new change note types target the readers who are downstream packagers "
"and project contributors. Additionally, the miscellaneous section is kept "
"for unspecified updates that do not fit anywhere else."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1328
msgid ""
"`#12502 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12502>`_: The UX of the "
"GitHub automation making pull requests to update the plugin list has been "
"updated. Previously, the maintainers had to close the automatically created "
"pull requests and re-open them to trigger the CI runs. From now on, they "
"only need to click the `Ready for review` button instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1337
msgid ""
"`#12522 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12522>`_: The ``:pull:"
"`` RST role has been replaced with a shorter ``:pr:`` due to starting to use "
"the implementation from the third-party :pypi:`sphinx-issues` Sphinx "
"extension -- by :user:`webknjaz`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1343
msgid ""
"`#12531 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12531>`_: The coverage "
"reporting configuration has been updated to exclude pytest's own tests "
"marked as expected to fail from the coverage report. This has an effect of "
"reducing the influence of flaky tests on the resulting number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1351
msgid ""
"`#12533 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12533>`_: The "
"``extlinks`` Sphinx extension is no longer enabled. The ``:bpo:`` role it "
"used to declare has been removed with that. BPO itself has migrated to "
"GitHub some years ago and it is possible to link the respective issues by "
"using their GitHub issue numbers and the ``:issue:`` role that the ``sphinx-"
"issues`` extension implements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1360
msgid ""
"`#12562 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12562>`_: Possible "
"typos in using the ``:user:`` RST role is now being linted through the pre-"
"commit tool integration -- by :user:`webknjaz`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1365
msgid "pytest 8.2.2 (2024-06-04)"
msgstr ""

