"`#12333 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12333>`_: pytest "
"releases are now attested using the recent `Artifact Attestation <https://"
"github.blog/2024-05-02-introducing-artifact-attestations-now-in-public-beta/"
">`_ support from GitHub, allowing users to verify the provenance of pytest's "
"sdist and wheel artifacts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1426
msgid "pytest 8.2.0 (2024-04-27)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1429 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1742
#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2684 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2845
#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3403 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3631
#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3831 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3915
#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4390
msgid "Breaking Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1431
msgid ""
"`#12089 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/pull/12089>`_: pytest now "
"requires that :class:`unittest.TestCase` subclasses can be instantiated "
"freely using ``MyTestCase('runTest')``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1433
msgid ""
"If the class doesn't allow this, you may see an error during collection such "
"as ``AttributeError: 'MyTestCase' object has no attribute 'runTest'``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1435
msgid ""
"Classes which do not override ``__init__``, or do not access the test method "
"in ``__init__`` using ``getattr`` or similar, are unaffected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1437
msgid ""
"Classes which do should take care to not crash when ``\"runTest\"`` is "
"given, as is shown in `unittest.TestCases's implementation <https://github."
"com/python/cpython/blob/51aefc5bf907ddffaaf083ded0de773adcdf08c8/Lib/"
"unittest/case.py#L419-L426>`_. Alternatively, consider using :meth:`setUp "
"<unittest.TestCase.setUp>` instead of ``__init__``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1440
msgid ""
"If you run into this issue using ``tornado.AsyncTestCase``, please see "
"`issue 12263 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12263>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1442
msgid ""
"If you run into this issue using an abstract ``TestCase`` subclass, please "
"see `issue 12275 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/12275>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:1444
msgid ""
"Historical note: the effect of this change on custom TestCase "
"implementations was not properly considered initially, this is why it was "
"done in a minor release. We apologize for the inconvenience."
msgstr ""

