#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2948
msgid ""
"`#8242 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8242>`_: Raising :class:"
"`unittest.SkipTest` to skip collection of tests during the pytest collection "
"phase is deprecated. Use :func:`pytest.skip` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2951
msgid ""
"Note: This deprecation only relates to using :class:`unittest.SkipTest` "
"during test collection. You are probably not doing that. Ordinary usage of :"
"class:`unittest.SkipTest` / :meth:`unittest.TestCase.skipTest` / :func:"
"`unittest.skip` in unittest test cases is fully supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2956
msgid "This deprecation has been reverted in pytest 7.1.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2959
msgid ""
"`#8315 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8315>`_: Several "
"behaviors of :meth:`Parser.addoption <pytest.Parser.addoption>` are now "
"scheduled for removal in pytest 8 (deprecated since pytest 2.4.0):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2962
msgid ""
"``parser.addoption(..., help=\".. %default ..\")`` - use ``%(default)s`` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2963
msgid ""
"``parser.addoption(..., type=\"int/string/float/complex\")`` - use "
"``type=int`` etc. instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2966
msgid ""
"`#8447 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8447>`_: Defining a "
"custom pytest node type which is both an :class:`~pytest.Item` and a :class:"
"`~pytest.Collector` (e.g. :class:`~pytest.File`) now issues a warning. It "
"was never sanely supported and triggers hard to debug errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2969
msgid ""
"See :ref:`the deprecation note <diamond-inheritance-deprecated>` for full "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2972
msgid ""
"`#8592 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8592>`_: "
"``pytest_cmdline_preparse`` has been officially deprecated.  It will be "
"removed in a future release.  Use :hook:`pytest_load_initial_conftests` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2974
msgid ""
"See :ref:`the deprecation note <cmdline-preparse-deprecated>` for full "
"details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2977
msgid ""
"`#8645 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8645>`_: :func:`pytest."
"warns(None) <pytest.warns>` is now deprecated because many people used it to "
"mean \"this code does not emit warnings\", but it actually had the effect of "
"checking that the code emits at least one warning of any type - like "
"``pytest.warns()`` or ``pytest.warns(Warning)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2983
msgid ""
"`#8948 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8948>`_: :func:`pytest."
"skip(msg=...) <pytest.skip>`, :func:`pytest.fail(msg=...) <pytest.fail>` "
"and :func:`pytest.exit(msg=...) <pytest.exit>` signatures now accept a "
"``reason`` argument instead of ``msg``.  Using ``msg`` still works, but is "
"deprecated and will be removed in a future release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2986
msgid ""
"This was changed for consistency with :func:`pytest.mark.skip <pytest.mark."
"skip>` and  :func:`pytest.mark.xfail <pytest.mark.xfail>` which both accept "
"``reason`` as an argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2989
msgid ""
"`#8174 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8174>`_: The following "
"changes have been made to types reachable through :attr:`pytest."
"ExceptionInfo.traceback`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2991
msgid ""
"The ``path`` property of ``_pytest.code.Code`` returns ``Path`` instead of "
"``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2992
msgid ""
"The ``path`` property of ``_pytest.code.TracebackEntry`` returns ``Path`` "
"instead of ``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:2994
msgid "There was no deprecation period for this change (sorry!)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3000
msgid ""
"`#5196 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5196>`_: Tests are now "
"ordered by definition order in more cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3002
msgid ""
"In a class hierarchy, tests from base classes are now consistently ordered "
"before tests defined on their subclasses (reverse MRO order)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3005
msgid ""
"`#7132 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7132>`_: Added two "
"environment variables :envvar:`PYTEST_THEME` and :envvar:`PYTEST_THEME_MODE` "
"to let the users customize the pygments theme used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3008
msgid ""
"`#7259 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7259>`_: Added :meth:"
"`cache.mkdir() <pytest.Cache.mkdir>`, which is similar to the existing "
"``cache.makedir()``, but returns a :class:`pathlib.Path` instead of a legacy "
"``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3011
msgid ""
"Added a ``paths`` type to :meth:`parser.addini() <pytest.Parser.addini>`, as "
"in ``parser.addini(\"mypaths\", \"my paths\", type=\"paths\")``, which is "
"similar to the existing ``pathlist``, but returns a list of :class:`pathlib."
"Path` instead of legacy ``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3017
msgid ""
"`#7469 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7469>`_: The types of "
"objects used in pytest's API are now exported so they may be used in type "
"annotations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3019
msgid "The newly-exported types are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3021
msgid "``pytest.Config`` for :class:`Config <pytest.Config>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3022
msgid "``pytest.Mark`` for :class:`marks <pytest.Mark>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3023
msgid ""
"``pytest.MarkDecorator`` for :class:`mark decorators <pytest.MarkDecorator>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3024
msgid ""
"``pytest.MarkGenerator`` for the :class:`pytest.mark <pytest.MarkGenerator>` "
"singleton."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3025
msgid ""
"``pytest.Metafunc`` for the :class:`metafunc <pytest.MarkGenerator>` "
"argument to the :hook:`pytest_generate_tests` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3026
msgid ""
"``pytest.CallInfo`` for the :class:`CallInfo <pytest.CallInfo>` type passed "
"to various hooks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3027
msgid ""
"``pytest.PytestPluginManager`` for :class:`PytestPluginManager <pytest."
"PytestPluginManager>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3028
msgid ""
"``pytest.ExceptionInfo`` for the :class:`ExceptionInfo <pytest."
"ExceptionInfo>` type returned from :func:`pytest.raises` and passed to "
"various hooks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3029
msgid ""
"``pytest.Parser`` for the :class:`Parser <pytest.Parser>` type passed to "
"the :hook:`pytest_addoption` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3030
msgid ""
"``pytest.OptionGroup`` for the :class:`OptionGroup <pytest.OptionGroup>` "
"type returned from the :func:`parser.addgroup <pytest.Parser.getgroup>` "
"method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3031
msgid ""
"``pytest.HookRecorder`` for the :class:`HookRecorder <pytest.HookRecorder>` "
"type returned from :class:`~pytest.Pytester`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3032
msgid ""
"``pytest.RecordedHookCall`` for the :class:`RecordedHookCall <pytest."
"HookRecorder>` type returned from :class:`~pytest.HookRecorder`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3033
msgid ""
"``pytest.RunResult`` for the :class:`RunResult <pytest.RunResult>` type "
"returned from :class:`~pytest.Pytester`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3034
msgid ""
"``pytest.LineMatcher`` for the :class:`LineMatcher <pytest.LineMatcher>` "
"type used in :class:`~pytest.RunResult` and others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3035
msgid ""
"``pytest.TestReport`` for the :class:`TestReport <pytest.TestReport>` type "
"used in various hooks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3036
msgid ""
"``pytest.CollectReport`` for the :class:`CollectReport <pytest."
"CollectReport>` type used in various hooks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3038
msgid ""
"Constructing most of them directly is not supported; they are only meant for "
"use in type annotations. Doing so will emit a deprecation warning, and may "
"become a hard-error in pytest 8.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3041 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3517
msgid ""
"Subclassing them is also not supported. This is not currently enforced at "
"runtime, but is detected by type-checkers such as mypy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3044
msgid ""
"`#7856 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7856>`_: :ref:`--import-"
"mode=importlib <import-modes>` now works with features that depend on "
"modules being on :py:data:`sys.modules`, such as :mod:`pickle` and :mod:"
"`dataclasses`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3048
msgid ""
"`#8144 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8144>`_: The following "
"hooks now receive an additional ``pathlib.Path`` argument, equivalent to an "
"existing ``py.path.local`` argument:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3050
msgid ""
":hook:`pytest_ignore_collect` - The ``collection_path`` parameter "
"(equivalent to existing ``path`` parameter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3051
msgid ""
":hook:`pytest_collect_file` - The ``file_path`` parameter (equivalent to "
"existing ``path`` parameter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3052
msgid ""
":hook:`pytest_pycollect_makemodule` - The ``module_path`` parameter "
"(equivalent to existing ``path`` parameter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3053
msgid ""
":hook:`pytest_report_header` - The ``start_path`` parameter (equivalent to "
"existing ``startdir`` parameter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3054
msgid ""
":hook:`pytest_report_collectionfinish` - The ``start_path`` parameter "
"(equivalent to existing ``startdir`` parameter)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3066
msgid ""
"`#8251 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8251>`_: Implement "
"``Node.path`` as a ``pathlib.Path``. Both the old ``fspath`` and this new "
"attribute gets set no matter whether ``path`` or ``fspath`` (deprecated) is "
"passed to the constructor. It is a replacement for the ``fspath`` attribute "
"(which represents the same path as ``py.path.local``). While ``fspath`` is "
"not deprecated yet due to the ongoing migration of methods like :meth:"
"`~pytest.Item.reportinfo`, we expect to deprecate it in a future release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3079
msgid ""
"`#8421 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8421>`_: :func:`pytest."
"approx` now works on :class:`~decimal.Decimal` within mappings/dicts and "
"sequences/lists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3082
msgid ""
"`#8606 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8606>`_: pytest "
"invocations with ``--fixtures-per-test`` and ``--fixtures`` have been "
"enriched with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3084
msgid "Fixture location path printed with the fixture name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3085
msgid ""
"First section of the fixture's docstring printed under the fixture name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3086
msgid ""
"Whole of fixture's docstring printed under the fixture name using ``--"
"verbose`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3089
msgid ""
"`#8761 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8761>`_: New :ref:"
"`version-tuple` attribute, which makes it simpler for users to do something "
"depending on the pytest version (such as declaring hooks which are "
"introduced in later versions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3092
msgid ""
"`#8789 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8789>`_: Switch TOML "
"parser from ``toml`` to ``tomli`` for TOML v1.0.0 support in ``pyproject."
"toml``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3095
msgid ""
"`#8920 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8920>`_: Added :class:"
"`pytest.Stash`, a facility for plugins to store their data on :class:"
"`~pytest.Config` and :class:`~_pytest.nodes.Node`\\s in a type-safe and "
"conflict-free manner. See :ref:`plugin-stash` for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3099
msgid ""
"`#8953 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8953>`_: :class:`~pytest."
"RunResult` method :meth:`~pytest.RunResult.assert_outcomes` now accepts a "
"``warnings`` argument to assert the total number of warnings captured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3103
msgid ""
"`#8954 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8954>`_: ``--debug`` "
"flag now accepts a :class:`str` file to route debug logs into, remains "
"defaulted to `pytestdebug.log`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3106
msgid ""
"`#9023 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9023>`_: Full diffs are "
"now always shown for equality assertions of iterables when `CI` or "
"``BUILD_NUMBER`` is found in the environment, even when ``-v`` isn't used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3111
msgid ""
"`#9113 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9113>`_: :class:`~pytest."
"RunResult` method :meth:`~pytest.RunResult.assert_outcomes` now accepts a "
"``deselected`` argument to assert the total number of deselected tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3115
msgid ""
"`#9114 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9114>`_: Added :confval:"
"`pythonpath` setting that adds listed paths to :data:`sys.path` for the "
"duration of the test session. If you currently use the pytest-pythonpath or "
"pytest-srcpaths plugins, you should be able to replace them with built-in "
"`pythonpath` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3122
msgid ""
"`#7480 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7480>`_: A deprecation "
"scheduled to be removed in a major version X (e.g. pytest 7, 8, 9, ...) now "
"uses warning category `PytestRemovedInXWarning`, a subclass of :class:"
"`~pytest.PytestDeprecationWarning`, instead of :class:`~pytest."
"PytestDeprecationWarning` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3126
msgid "See :ref:`backwards-compatibility` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3129
msgid ""
"`#7864 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7864>`_: Improved error "
"messages when parsing warning filters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3131
msgid ""
"Previously pytest would show an internal traceback, which besides being ugly "
"sometimes would hide the cause of the problem (for example an "
"``ImportError`` while importing a specific warning type)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3135
msgid ""
"`#8335 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8335>`_: Improved :func:"
"`pytest.approx` assertion messages for sequences of numbers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3137
msgid ""
"The assertion messages now dumps a table with the index and the error of "
"each diff. Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3140
msgid ""
">       assert [1, 2, 3, 4] == pytest.approx([1, 3, 3, 5])\n"
"E       assert comparison failed for 2 values:\n"
"E         Index | Obtained | Expected\n"
"E         1     | 2        | 3 +- 3.0e-06\n"
"E         3     | 4        | 5 +- 5.0e-06"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3147
msgid ""
"`#8403 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8403>`_: By default, "
"pytest will truncate long strings in assert errors so they don't clutter the "
"output too much, currently at ``240`` characters by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3150
msgid ""
"However, in some cases the longer output helps, or is even crucial, to "
"diagnose a failure. Using ``-v`` will now increase the truncation threshold "
"to ``2400`` characters, and ``-vv`` or higher will disable truncation "
"entirely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3154
msgid ""
"`#8509 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8509>`_: Fixed issue "
"where :meth:`unittest.TestCase.setUpClass` is not called when a test has `/` "
"in its name since pytest 6.2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3156
msgid ""
"This refers to the path part in pytest node IDs, e.g. ``TestClass::test_it`` "
"in the node ID ``tests/test_file.py::TestClass::test_it``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3158
msgid ""
"Now, instead of assuming that the test name does not contain ``/``, it is "
"assumed that test path does not contain ``::``. We plan to hopefully make "
"both of these work in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3161
msgid ""
"`#8803 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8803>`_: It is now "
"possible to add colors to custom log levels on cli log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3163
msgid ""
"By using ``add_color_level`` from a :hook:`pytest_configure` hook, colors "
"can be added::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3165
msgid ""
"logging_plugin = config.pluginmanager.get_plugin('logging-plugin')\n"
"logging_plugin.log_cli_handler.formatter.add_color_level(logging.INFO, "
"'cyan')\n"
"logging_plugin.log_cli_handler.formatter.add_color_level(logging.SPAM, "
"'blue')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3169
msgid "See :ref:`log_colors` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3172
msgid ""
"`#8822 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8822>`_: When showing "
"fixture paths in `--fixtures` or `--fixtures-by-test`, fixtures coming from "
"pytest itself now display an elided path, rather than the full path to the "
"file in the `site-packages` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3175
msgid ""
"`#8898 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8898>`_: Complex numbers "
"are now treated like floats and integers when generating parameterization "
"IDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3178
msgid ""
"`#9062 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9062>`_: ``--stepwise-"
"skip`` now implicitly enables ``--stepwise`` and can be used on its own."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3181
msgid ""
"`#9205 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9205>`_: :meth:`pytest."
"Cache.set` now preserves key order when saving dicts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3188
msgid ""
"`#7124 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/7124>`_: Fixed an issue "
"where ``__main__.py`` would raise an ``ImportError`` when ``--doctest-"
"modules`` was provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3191
msgid ""
"`#8061 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8061>`_: Fixed failing "
"``staticmethod`` test cases if they are inherited from a parent test class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3194
msgid ""
"`#8192 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8192>`_: ``testdir."
"makefile`` now silently accepts values which don't start with ``.`` to "
"maintain backward compatibility with older pytest versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3196
msgid ""
"``pytester.makefile`` now issues a clearer error if the ``.`` is missing in "
"the ``ext`` argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3199
msgid ""
"`#8258 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8258>`_: Fixed issue "
"where pytest's ``faulthandler`` support would not dump traceback on crashes "
"if the :mod:`faulthandler` module was already enabled during pytest startup "
"(using ``python -X dev -m pytest`` for example)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3204
msgid ""
"`#8317 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8317>`_: Fixed an issue "
"where illegal directory characters derived from ``getpass.getuser()`` raised "
"an ``OSError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3207
msgid ""
"`#8367 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8367>`_: Fix ``Class."
"from_parent`` so it forwards extra keyword arguments to the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3210
msgid ""
"`#8377 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8377>`_: The test "
"selection options ``pytest -k`` and ``pytest -m`` now support matching names "
"containing forward slash (``/``) characters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3214
msgid ""
"`#8384 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8384>`_: The ``@pytest."
"mark.skip`` decorator now correctly handles its arguments. When the "
"``reason`` argument is accidentally given both positional and as a keyword "
"(e.g. because it was confused with ``skipif``), a ``TypeError`` now occurs. "
"Before, such tests were silently skipped, and the positional argument "
"ignored. Additionally, ``reason`` is now documented correctly as positional "
"or keyword (rather than keyword-only)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3217
msgid ""
"`#8394 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8394>`_: Use private "
"names for internal fixtures that handle classic setup/teardown so that they "
"don't show up with the default ``--fixtures`` invocation (but they still "
"show up with ``--fixtures -v``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3220
msgid ""
"`#8456 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8456>`_: The :confval:"
"`required_plugins` config option now works correctly when pre-releases of "
"plugins are installed, rather than falsely claiming that those plugins "
"aren't installed at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3223
msgid ""
"`#8464 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8464>`_: ``-c <config "
"file>`` now also properly defines ``rootdir`` as the directory that contains "
"``<config file>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3226
msgid ""
"`#8503 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8503>`_: :meth:`pytest."
"MonkeyPatch.syspath_prepend` no longer fails when ``setuptools`` is not "
"installed. It now only calls ``pkg_resources.fixup_namespace_packages`` if "
"``pkg_resources`` was previously imported, because it is not needed "
"otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3232
msgid ""
"`#8548 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8548>`_: Introduce fix "
"to handle precision width in ``log-cli-format`` in turn to fix output "
"coloring for certain formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3235
msgid ""
"`#8796 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8796>`_: Fixed internal "
"error when skipping doctests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3238
msgid ""
"`#8983 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8983>`_: The test "
"selection options ``pytest -k`` and ``pytest -m`` now support matching names "
"containing backslash (`\\\\`) characters. Backslashes are treated literally, "
"not as escape characters (the values being matched against are already "
"escaped)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3242
msgid ""
"`#8990 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8990>`_: Fix `pytest -"
"vv` crashing with an internal exception `AttributeError: 'str' object has no "
"attribute 'relative_to'` in some cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3245
msgid ""
"`#9077 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9077>`_: Fixed confusing "
"error message when ``request.fspath`` / ``request.path`` was accessed from a "
"session-scoped fixture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3248
msgid ""
"`#9131 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9131>`_: Fixed the URL "
"used by ``--pastebin`` to use `bpa.st <http://bpa.st>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3251
msgid ""
"`#9163 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9163>`_: The end line "
"number and end column offset are now properly set for rewritten assert "
"statements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3254
msgid ""
"`#9169 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9169>`_: Support for the "
"``files`` API from ``importlib.resources`` within rewritten files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3257
msgid ""
"`#9272 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9272>`_: The nose "
"compatibility module-level fixtures `setup()` and `teardown()` are now only "
"called once per module, instead of for each test function. They are now "
"called even if object-level `setup`/`teardown` is defined."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3265
msgid ""
"`#4320 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/4320>`_: Improved docs "
"for `pytester.copy_example`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3268
msgid ""
"`#5105 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5105>`_: Add "
"automatically generated :ref:`plugin-list`. The list is updated on a "
"periodic schedule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3271
msgid ""
"`#8337 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8337>`_: Recommend "
"`numpy.testing <https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/routines.testing."
"html>`__ module on :func:`pytest.approx` documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3274
msgid ""
"`#8655 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8655>`_: Help text for "
"``--pdbcls`` more accurately reflects the option's behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3277
msgid ""
"`#9210 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9210>`_: Remove "
"incorrect docs about ``confcutdir`` being a configuration option: it can "
"only be set through the ``--confcutdir`` command-line option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3280
msgid ""
"`#9242 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9242>`_: Upgrade "
"readthedocs configuration to use a `newer Ubuntu version <https://blog."
"readthedocs.com/new-build-specification/>`__` with better unicode support "
"for PDF docs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3283
msgid ""
"`#9341 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9341>`_: Various methods "
"commonly used for :ref:`non-python tests` are now correctly documented in "
"the reference docs. They were undocumented previously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3290
msgid ""
"`#8133 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8133>`_: Migrate to "
"``setuptools_scm`` 6.x to use ``SETUPTOOLS_SCM_PRETEND_VERSION_FOR_PYTEST`` "
"for more robust release tooling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3293
msgid ""
"`#8174 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8174>`_: The following "
"changes have been made to internal pytest types/functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3295
msgid ""
"The ``_pytest.code.getfslineno()`` function returns ``Path`` instead of ``py."
"path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3296
msgid ""
"The ``_pytest.python.path_matches_patterns()`` function takes ``Path`` "
"instead of ``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3297
msgid ""
"The ``_pytest._code.Traceback.cut()`` function accepts any ``os."
"PathLike[str]``, not just ``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3300
msgid ""
"`#8248 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8248>`_: Internal "
"Restructure: let ``python.PyObjMixin`` inherit from ``nodes.Node`` to carry "
"over typing information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3303
msgid ""
"`#8432 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8432>`_: Improve error "
"message when :func:`pytest.skip` is used at module level without passing "
"`allow_module_level=True`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3306
msgid ""
"`#8818 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8818>`_: Ensure "
"``regendoc`` opts out of ``TOX_ENV`` cachedir selection to ensure "
"independent example test runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3309
msgid ""
"`#8913 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8913>`_: The private "
"``CallSpec2._arg2scopenum`` attribute has been removed after an internal "
"refactoring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3312
msgid ""
"`#8967 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/8967>`_: :hook:"
"`pytest_assertion_pass` is no longer considered experimental and future "
"changes to it will be considered more carefully."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3316
msgid ""
"`#9202 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9202>`_: Add github "
"action to upload coverage report to codecov instead of bash uploader."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3319
msgid ""
"`#9225 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9225>`_: Changed the "
"command used to create sdist and wheel artifacts: using the build package "
"instead of setup.py."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3322
msgid ""
"`#9351 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/9351>`_: Correct minor "
"typos in doc/en/example/special.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3326
msgid "pytest 6.2.5 (2021-08-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3332
msgid ":issue:`8494`: Python 3.10 is now supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3335
msgid ":issue:`9040`: Enable compatibility with ``pluggy 1.0`` or later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3339
msgid "pytest 6.2.4 (2021-05-04)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3344
msgid ":issue:`8539`: Fixed assertion rewriting on Python 3.10."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3348
msgid "pytest 6.2.3 (2021-04-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3353
msgid ""
":issue:`8414`: pytest used to create directories under ``/tmp`` with world-"
"readable permissions. This means that any user in the system was able to "
"read information written by tests in temporary directories (such as those "
"created by the ``tmp_path``/``tmpdir`` fixture). Now the directories are "
"created with private permissions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3359
msgid ""
"pytest used to silently use a preexisting ``/tmp/pytest-of-<username>`` "
"directory, even if owned by another user. This means another user could pre-"
"create such a directory and gain control of another user's temporary "
"directory. Now such a condition results in an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3366
msgid "pytest 6.2.2 (2021-01-25)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3371
msgid ""
":issue:`8152`: Fixed \"(<Skipped instance>)\" being shown as a skip reason "
"in the verbose test summary line when the reason is empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3374
msgid ""
":issue:`8249`: Fix the ``faulthandler`` plugin for occasions when running "
"with ``twisted.logger`` and using ``pytest --capture=no``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3378
msgid "pytest 6.2.1 (2020-12-15)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3383
msgid ""
":issue:`7678`: Fixed bug where ``ImportPathMismatchError`` would be raised "
"for files compiled in the host and loaded later from an UNC mounted path "
"(Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3387
msgid ""
":issue:`8132`: Fixed regression in ``approx``: in 6.2.0 ``approx`` no longer "
"raises ``TypeError`` when dealing with non-numeric types, falling back to "
"normal comparison. Before 6.2.0, array types like tf.DeviceArray fell "
"through to the scalar case, and happened to compare correctly to a scalar if "
"they had only one element. After 6.2.0, these types began failing, because "
"they inherited neither from standard Python number hierarchy nor from "
"``numpy.ndarray``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3394
msgid ""
"``approx`` now converts arguments to ``numpy.ndarray`` if they expose the "
"array protocol and are not scalars. This treats array-like objects like "
"numpy arrays, regardless of size."
msgstr ""

