msgid ""
"These have always been considered private, but now issue a deprecation "
"warning, which may become a hard error in pytest 8.0.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3432
msgid ""
":issue:`7530`: The ``--strict`` command-line option has been deprecated, use "
"``--strict-markers`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3434
msgid ""
"We have plans to maybe in the future to reintroduce ``--strict`` and make it "
"an encompassing flag for all strictness related options (``--strict-"
"markers`` and ``--strict-config`` at the moment, more might be introduced in "
"the future)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3438
msgid ""
":issue:`7988`: The ``@pytest.yield_fixture`` decorator/function is now "
"deprecated. Use :func:`pytest.fixture` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3440
msgid ""
"``yield_fixture`` has been an alias for ``fixture`` for a very long time, so "
"can be search/replaced safely."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3447
msgid ""
":issue:`5299`: pytest now warns about unraisable exceptions and unhandled "
"thread exceptions that occur in tests on Python>=3.8. See :ref:`unraisable` "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3451
msgid ""
":issue:`7425`: New :fixture:`pytester` fixture, which is identical to :"
"fixture:`testdir` but its methods return :class:`pathlib.Path` when "
"appropriate instead of ``py.path.local``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3453
msgid ""
"This is part of the movement to use :class:`pathlib.Path` objects "
"internally, in order to remove the dependency to ``py`` in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3455
msgid ""
"Internally, the old ``pytest.Testdir`` is now a thin wrapper around :class:"
"`~pytest.Pytester`, preserving the old interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3458
msgid ""
":issue:`7695`: A new hook was added, `pytest_markeval_namespace` which "
"should return a dictionary. This dictionary will be used to augment the "
"\"global\" variables available to evaluate skipif/xfail/xpass markers."
msgstr ""

