#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3526
msgid ""
":issue:`7701`: Improved reporting when using ``--collected-only``. It will "
"now show the number of collected tests in the summary stats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3529
msgid ""
":issue:`7710`: Use strict equality comparison for non-numeric types in :func:"
"`pytest.approx` instead of raising :class:`TypeError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3532
msgid ""
"This was the undocumented behavior before 3.7, but is now officially a "
"supported feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3535
msgid ""
":issue:`7938`: New ``--sw-skip`` argument which is a shorthand for ``--"
"stepwise-skip``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3538
msgid ""
":issue:`8023`: Added ``'node_modules'`` to default value for :confval:"
"`norecursedirs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3541
msgid ""
":issue:`8032`: :meth:`doClassCleanups <unittest.TestCase.doClassCleanups>` "
"(introduced in :mod:`unittest` in Python and 3.8) is now called "
"appropriately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3548
msgid ""
":issue:`4824`: Fixed quadratic behavior and improved performance of "
"collection of items using autouse fixtures and xunit fixtures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3551 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3602
msgid ""
":issue:`7758`: Fixed an issue where some files in packages are getting lost "
"from ``--lf`` even though they contain tests that failed. Regressed in "
"pytest 5.4.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3554
msgid ""
":issue:`7911`: Directories created by by :fixture:`tmp_path` and :fixture:"
"`tmpdir` are now considered stale after 3 days without modification "
"(previous value was 3 hours) to avoid deleting directories still in use in "
"long running test suites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3557
msgid ""
":issue:`7913`: Fixed a crash or hang in :meth:`pytester.spawn <pytest."
"Pytester.spawn>` when the :mod:`readline` module is involved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3560
msgid ""
":issue:`7951`: Fixed handling of recursive symlinks when collecting tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3563
msgid ""
":issue:`7981`: Fixed symlinked directories not being followed during "
"collection. Regressed in pytest 6.1.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3566
msgid ""
":issue:`8016`: Fixed only one doctest being collected when using ``pytest --"
"doctest-modules path/to/an/__init__.py``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3573
msgid ""
":issue:`7429`: Add more information and use cases about skipping doctests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3576
msgid ""
":issue:`7780`: Classes which should not be inherited from are now marked "
"``final class`` in the API reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3579
msgid ""
":issue:`7872`: ``_pytest.config.argparsing.Parser.addini()`` accepts "
"explicit ``None`` and ``\"string\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3582
msgid ""
":issue:`7878`: In pull request section, ask to commit after editing "
"changelog and authors file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3589
msgid ""
":issue:`7802`: The ``attrs`` dependency requirement is now >=19.2.0 instead "
"of >=17.4.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3592
msgid ""
":issue:`8014`: `.pyc` files created by pytest's assertion rewriting now "
"conform to the newer :pep:`552` format on Python>=3.7. (These files are "
"internal and only interpreted by pytest itself.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3597
msgid "pytest 6.1.2 (2020-10-28)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3605
msgid ""
":issue:`7911`: Directories created by `tmpdir` are now considered stale "
"after 3 days without modification (previous value was 3 hours) to avoid "
"deleting directories still in use in long running test suites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3612
msgid ""
":issue:`7815`: Improve deprecation warning message for ``pytest."
"_fillfuncargs()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3616
msgid "pytest 6.1.1 (2020-10-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3621
msgid ""
":issue:`7807`: Fixed regression in pytest 6.1.0 causing incorrect rootdir to "
"be determined in some non-trivial cases where parent directories have config "
"files as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3624
msgid ""
":issue:`7814`: Fixed crash in header reporting when :confval:`testpaths` is "
"used and contains absolute paths (regression in 6.1.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3628
msgid "pytest 6.1.0 (2020-09-26)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3633
msgid ""
":issue:`5585`: As per our policy, the following features which have been "
"deprecated in the 5.X series are now removed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3636
msgid ""
"The ``funcargnames`` read-only property of ``FixtureRequest``, ``Metafunc``, "
"and ``Function`` classes. Use ``fixturenames`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3638
msgid ""
"``@pytest.fixture`` no longer supports positional arguments, pass all "
"arguments by keyword instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3640
msgid ""
"Direct construction of ``Node`` subclasses now raise an error, use "
"``from_parent`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3642
msgid ""
"The default value for ``junit_family`` has changed to ``xunit2``. If you "
"require the old format, add ``junit_family=xunit1`` to your configuration "
"file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3644
msgid ""
"The ``TerminalReporter`` no longer has a ``writer`` attribute. Plugin "
"authors may use the public functions of the ``TerminalReporter`` instead of "
"accessing the ``TerminalWriter`` object directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3646
msgid ""
"The ``--result-log`` option has been removed. Users are recommended to use "
"the `pytest-reportlog <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-reportlog>`__ "
"plugin instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3649 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:5091
msgid "For more information consult :std:doc:`deprecations` in the docs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3656
msgid ""
":issue:`6981`: The ``pytest.collect`` module is deprecated: all its names "
"can be imported from ``pytest`` directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3659
msgid ""
":issue:`7097`: The ``pytest._fillfuncargs`` function is deprecated. This "
"function was kept for backward compatibility with an older plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3662
msgid ""
"It's functionality is not meant to be used directly, but if you must replace "
"it, use `function._request._fillfixtures()` instead, though note this is not "
"a public API and may break in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3667 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4017
msgid ""
":issue:`7210`: The special ``-k '-expr'`` syntax to ``-k`` is deprecated. "
"Use ``-k 'not expr'`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3670 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4020
msgid ""
"The special ``-k 'expr:'`` syntax to ``-k`` is deprecated. Please open an "
"issue if you use this and want a replacement."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3674
msgid ""
":issue:`7255`: The ``pytest_warning_captured`` hook is deprecated in favor "
"of :hook:`pytest_warning_recorded`, and will be removed in a future version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3678
msgid ""
":issue:`7648`: The ``gethookproxy()`` and ``isinitpath()`` methods of "
"``FSCollector`` and ``Package`` are deprecated; use ``self.session."
"gethookproxy()`` and ``self.session.isinitpath()`` instead. This should work "
"on all pytest versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3687
msgid ""
":issue:`7667`: New ``--durations-min`` command-line flag controls the "
"minimal duration for inclusion in the slowest list of tests shown by ``--"
"durations``. Previously this was hard-coded to ``0.005s``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3694
msgid ""
":issue:`6681`: Internal pytest warnings issued during the early stages of "
"initialization are now properly handled and can filtered through :confval:"
"`filterwarnings` or ``--pythonwarnings/-W``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3696
msgid ""
"This also fixes a number of long standing issues: :issue:`2891`, :issue:"
"`7620`, :issue:`7426`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3699
msgid ""
":issue:`7572`: When a plugin listed in ``required_plugins`` is missing or an "
"unknown config key is used with ``--strict-config``, a simple error message "
"is now shown instead of a stacktrace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3702
msgid ""
":issue:`7685`: Added two new attributes :attr:`rootpath <pytest.Config."
"rootpath>` and :attr:`inipath <pytest.Config.inipath>` to :class:`~pytest."
"Config`. These attributes are :class:`pathlib.Path` versions of the existing "
"``rootdir`` and ``inifile`` attributes, and should be preferred over them "
"when possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3707
msgid ""
":issue:`7780`: Public classes which are not designed to be inherited from "
"are now marked :func:`@final <typing.final>`. Code which inherits from these "
"classes will trigger a type-checking (e.g. mypy) error, but will still work "
"in runtime. Currently the ``final`` designation does not appear in the API "
"Reference but hopefully will in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3716
msgid ""
":issue:`1953`: Fixed error when overwriting a parametrized fixture, while "
"also reusing the super fixture value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3718
msgid ""
"# conftest.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture(params=[1, 2])\n"
"def foo(request):\n"
"    return request.param\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"# test_foo.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"@pytest.fixture\n"
"def foo(foo):\n"
"    return foo * 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3738
msgid ""
":issue:`4984`: Fixed an internal error crash with ``IndexError: list index "
"out of range`` when collecting a module which starts with a decorated "
"function, the decorator raises, and assertion rewriting is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3743
msgid ""
":issue:`7591`: pylint shouldn't complain anymore about unimplemented "
"abstract methods when inheriting from :ref:`File <non-python tests>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3746
msgid ""
":issue:`7628`: Fixed test collection when a full path without a drive letter "
"was passed to pytest on Windows (for example ``\\projects\\tests\\test.py`` "
"instead of ``c:\\projects\\tests\\pytest.py``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3749
msgid ""
":issue:`7638`: Fix handling of command-line options that appear as paths but "
"trigger an OS-level syntax error on Windows, such as the options used "
"internally by ``pytest-xdist``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3752
msgid ""
":issue:`7742`: Fixed INTERNALERROR when accessing locals / globals with "
"faulty ``exec``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3759
msgid ":issue:`1477`: Removed faq.rst and its reference in contents.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3766
msgid ""
":issue:`7536`: The internal ``junitxml`` plugin has rewritten to use ``xml."
"etree.ElementTree``. The order of attributes in XML elements might differ. "
"Some unneeded escaping is no longer performed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3771
msgid ""
":issue:`7587`: The dependency on the ``more-itertools`` package has been "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3774
msgid ""
":issue:`7631`: The result type of :meth:`capfd.readouterr() <pytest."
"CaptureFixture.readouterr>` (and similar) is no longer a namedtuple, but "
"should behave like one in all respects. This was done for technical reasons."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3778
msgid ""
":issue:`7671`: When collecting tests, pytest finds test classes and "
"functions by examining the attributes of python objects (modules, classes "
"and instances). To speed up this process, pytest now ignores builtin "
"attributes (like ``__class__``, ``__delattr__`` and ``__new__``) without "
"consulting the :confval:`python_classes` and :confval:`python_functions` "
"configuration options and without passing them to plugins using the :hook:"
"`pytest_pycollect_makeitem` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3787
msgid "pytest 6.0.2 (2020-09-04)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3792
msgid ""
":issue:`7148`: Fixed ``--log-cli`` potentially causing unrelated ``print`` "
"output to be swallowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3795
msgid ""
":issue:`7672`: Fixed log-capturing level restored incorrectly if ``caplog."
"set_level`` is called more than once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3798
msgid ""
":issue:`7686`: Fixed `NotSetType.token` being used as the parameter ID when "
"the parametrization list is empty. Regressed in pytest 6.0.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3802
msgid ""
":issue:`7707`: Fix internal error when handling some exceptions that contain "
"multiple lines or the style uses multiple lines (``--tb=line`` for example)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3806
msgid "pytest 6.0.1 (2020-07-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3811
msgid ""
":issue:`7394`: Passing an empty ``help`` value to ``Parser.add_option`` is "
"now accepted instead of crashing when running ``pytest --help``. Passing "
"``None`` raises a more informative ``TypeError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3815
msgid ""
":issue:`7558`: Fix pylint ``not-callable`` lint on ``pytest.mark."
"parametrize()`` and the other builtin marks: ``skip``, ``skipif``, "
"``xfail``, ``usefixtures``, ``filterwarnings``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3819
msgid ""
":issue:`7559`: Fix regression in plugins using ``TestReport.longreprtext`` "
"(such as ``pytest-html``) when ``TestReport.longrepr`` is not a string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3822
msgid ""
":issue:`7569`: Fix logging capture handler's level not reset on teardown "
"after a call to ``caplog.set_level()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3826
msgid "pytest 6.0.0 (2020-07-28)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3828
msgid ""
"(**Please see the full set of changes for this release also in the 6.0.0rc1 "
"notes below**)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3833
msgid ":issue:`5584`: **PytestDeprecationWarning are now errors by default.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3835 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:5261
msgid ""
"Following our plan to remove deprecated features with as little disruption "
"as possible, all warnings of type ``PytestDeprecationWarning`` now generate "
"errors instead of warning messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3839
msgid ""
"**The affected features will be effectively removed in pytest 6.1**, so "
"please consult the :std:doc:`deprecations` section in the docs for "
"directions on how to update existing code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3842
msgid ""
"In the pytest ``6.0.X`` series, it is possible to change the errors back "
"into warnings as a stopgap measure by adding this to your ``pytest.ini`` "
"file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3845 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:5271
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"filterwarnings =\n"
"    ignore::pytest.PytestDeprecationWarning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3851
msgid "But this will stop working when pytest ``6.1`` is released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3853
msgid ""
"**If you have concerns** about the removal of a specific feature, please add "
"a comment to :issue:`5584`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3857
msgid ""
":issue:`7472`: The ``exec_()`` and ``is_true()`` methods of ``_pytest._code."
"Frame`` have been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3864
msgid ""
":issue:`7464`: Added support for :envvar:`NO_COLOR` and :envvar:"
"`FORCE_COLOR` environment variables to control colored output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3871
msgid ""
":issue:`7467`: ``--log-file`` CLI option and ``log_file`` ini marker now "
"create subdirectories if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3874
msgid ""
":issue:`7489`: The :func:`pytest.raises` function has a clearer error "
"message when ``match`` equals the obtained string but is not a regex match. "
"In this case it is suggested to escape the regex."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3881
msgid ""
":issue:`7392`: Fix the reported location of tests skipped with ``@pytest."
"mark.skip`` when ``--runxfail`` is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3884
msgid ""
":issue:`7491`: :fixture:`tmpdir` and :fixture:`tmp_path` no longer raise an "
"error if the lock to check for stale temporary directories is not accessible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3888
msgid ":issue:`7517`: Preserve line endings when captured via ``capfd``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3891
msgid ""
":issue:`7534`: Restored the previous formatting of ``TracebackEntry."
"__str__`` which was changed by accident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3898
msgid ""
":issue:`7422`: Clarified when the ``usefixtures`` mark can apply fixtures to "
"test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3901
msgid ""
":issue:`7441`: Add a note about ``-q`` option used in getting started guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3908
msgid ""
":issue:`7389`: Fixture scope ``package`` is no longer considered "
"experimental."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3912
msgid "pytest 6.0.0rc1 (2020-07-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3917
msgid ""
":issue:`1316`: ``TestReport.longrepr`` is now always an instance of "
"``ReprExceptionInfo``. Previously it was a ``str`` when a test failed with "
"``pytest.fail(..., pytrace=False)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3920
msgid ""
":issue:`5965`: symlinks are no longer resolved during collection and "
"matching `conftest.py` files with test file paths."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3922
msgid ""
"Resolving symlinks for the current directory and during collection was "
"introduced as a bugfix in 3.9.0, but it actually is a new feature which had "
"unfortunate consequences in Windows and surprising results in other "
"platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3924
msgid ""
"The team decided to step back on resolving symlinks at all, planning to "
"review this in the future with a more solid solution (see discussion in :pr:"
"`6523` for details)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3927
msgid ""
"This might break test suites which made use of this feature; the fix is to "
"create a symlink for the entire test tree, and not only to partial files/"
"tress as it was possible previously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3931
msgid ""
":issue:`6505`: ``Testdir.run().parseoutcomes()`` now always returns the "
"parsed nouns in plural form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3933
msgid ""
"Originally ``parseoutcomes()`` would always returns the nouns in plural "
"form, but a change meant to improve the terminal summary by using singular "
"form single items (``1 warning`` or ``1 error``) caused an unintended "
"regression by changing the keys returned by ``parseoutcomes()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3937
msgid ""
"Now the API guarantees to always return the plural form, so calls like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3939
msgid ""
"result = testdir.runpytest()\n"
"result.assert_outcomes(error=1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3944
msgid "Need to be changed to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3947
msgid ""
"result = testdir.runpytest()\n"
"result.assert_outcomes(errors=1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3953
msgid ""
":issue:`6903`: The ``os.dup()`` function is now assumed to exist. We are not "
"aware of any supported Python 3 implementations which do not provide it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3957
msgid ""
":issue:`7040`: ``-k`` no longer matches against the names of the directories "
"outside the test session root."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3959
msgid ""
"Also, ``pytest.Package.name`` is now just the name of the directory "
"containing the package's ``__init__.py`` file, instead of the full path. "
"This is consistent with how the other nodes are named, and also one of the "
"reasons why ``-k`` would match against any directory containing the test "
"suite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3965
msgid ""
":issue:`7122`: Expressions given to the ``-m`` and ``-k`` options are no "
"longer evaluated using Python's :func:`eval`. The format supports ``or``, "
"``and``, ``not``, parenthesis and general identifiers to match against. "
"Python constants, keywords or other operators are no longer evaluated "
"differently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3970
msgid ""
":issue:`7135`: Pytest now uses its own ``TerminalWriter`` class instead of "
"using the one from the ``py`` library. Plugins generally access this class "
"through ``TerminalReporter.writer``, ``TerminalReporter.write()`` (and "
"similar methods), or ``_pytest.config.create_terminal_writer()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3974
msgid "The following breaking changes were made:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3976
msgid ""
"Output (``write()`` method and others) no longer flush implicitly; the "
"flushing behavior of the underlying file is respected. To flush explicitly "
"(for example, if you want output to be shown before an end-of-line is "
"printed), use ``write(flush=True)`` or ``terminal_writer.flush()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3980
msgid ""
"Explicit Windows console support was removed, delegated to the colorama "
"library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3981
msgid "Support for writing ``bytes`` was removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3982
msgid ""
"The ``reline`` method and ``chars_on_current_line`` property were removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3983
msgid "The ``stringio`` and ``encoding`` arguments was removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3984
msgid "Support for passing a callable instead of a file was removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3987
msgid ""
":issue:`7224`: The `item.catch_log_handler` and `item.catch_log_handlers` "
"attributes, set by the logging plugin and never meant to be public, are no "
"longer available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3990
msgid ""
"The deprecated ``--no-print-logs`` option and ``log_print`` ini option are "
"removed. Use ``--show-capture`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3993
msgid ""
":issue:`7226`: Removed the unused ``args`` parameter from ``pytest.Function."
"__init__``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:3996
msgid ""
":issue:`7418`: Removed the `pytest_doctest_prepare_content` hook "
"specification. This hook hasn't been triggered by pytest for at least 10 "
"years."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4000
msgid ""
":issue:`7438`: Some changes were made to the internal ``_pytest._code."
"source``, listed here for the benefit of plugin authors who may be using it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4003
msgid ""
"The ``deindent`` argument to ``Source()`` has been removed, now it is always "
"true."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4004
msgid ""
"Support for zero or multiple arguments to ``Source()`` has been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4005
msgid "Support for comparing ``Source`` with an ``str`` has been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4006
msgid ""
"The methods ``Source.isparseable()`` and ``Source.putaround()`` have been "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4007
msgid ""
"The method ``Source.compile()`` and function ``_pytest._code.compile()`` "
"have been removed; use plain ``compile()`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4009
msgid ""
"The function ``_pytest._code.source.getsource()`` has been removed; use "
"``Source()`` directly instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4023
msgid ""
":issue:`4049`: ``pytest_warning_captured`` is deprecated in favor of the "
"``pytest_warning_recorded`` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4029
msgid ""
":issue:`1556`: pytest now supports ``pyproject.toml`` files for "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4031
msgid ""
"The configuration options is similar to the one available in other formats, "
"but must be defined in a ``[tool.pytest.ini_options]`` table to be picked up "
"by pytest:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4034
msgid ""
"# pyproject.toml\n"
"[tool.pytest.ini_options]\n"
"minversion = \"6.0\"\n"
"addopts = \"-ra -q\"\n"
"testpaths = [\n"
"    \"tests\",\n"
"    \"integration\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4045
msgid "More information can be found :ref:`in the docs <config file formats>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4048
msgid ""
":issue:`3342`: pytest now includes inline type annotations and exposes them "
"to user programs. Most of the user-facing API is covered, as well as "
"internal code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4051
msgid ""
"If you are running a type checker such as mypy on your tests, you may start "
"noticing type errors indicating incorrect usage. If you run into an error "
"that you believe to be incorrect, please let us know in an issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4055
msgid ""
"The types were developed against mypy version 0.780. Versions before 0.750 "
"are known not to work. We recommend using the latest version. Other type "
"checkers may work as well, but they are not officially verified to work by "
"pytest yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4061
msgid ""
":issue:`4049`: Introduced a new hook named `pytest_warning_recorded` to "
"convey information about warnings captured by the internal `pytest` warnings "
"plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4063
msgid ""
"This hook is meant to replace `pytest_warning_captured`, which is deprecated "
"and will be removed in a future release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4066
msgid ":issue:`6471`: New command-line flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4068
msgid ""
"`--no-header`: disables the initial header, including platform, version, and "
"plugins."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4069
msgid "`--no-summary`: disables the final test summary, including warnings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4072
msgid ""
":issue:`6856`: A warning is now shown when an unknown key is read from a "
"config INI file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4074
msgid ""
"The `--strict-config` flag has been added to treat these warnings as errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4077
msgid ""
":issue:`6906`: Added `--code-highlight` command line option to enable/"
"disable code highlighting in terminal output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4080
msgid ""
":issue:`7245`: New ``--import-mode=importlib`` option that uses :mod:"
"`importlib` to import test modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4082
msgid ""
"Traditionally pytest used ``__import__`` while changing ``sys.path`` to "
"import test modules (which also changes ``sys.modules`` as a side-effect), "
"which works but has a number of drawbacks, like requiring test modules that "
"don't live in packages to have unique names (as they need to reside under a "
"unique name in ``sys.modules``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4086
msgid ""
"``--import-mode=importlib`` uses more fine-grained import mechanisms from "
"``importlib`` which don't require pytest to change ``sys.path`` or ``sys."
"modules`` at all, eliminating much of the drawbacks of the previous mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4090
msgid ""
"We intend to make ``--import-mode=importlib`` the default in future "
"versions, so users are encouraged to try the new mode and provide feedback "
"(both positive or negative) in issue :issue:`7245`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4093
msgid ""
"You can read more about this option in :std:ref:`the documentation <import-"
"modes>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4096
msgid ""
":issue:`7305`: New ``required_plugins`` configuration option allows the user "
"to specify a list of plugins, including version information, that are "
"required for pytest to run. An error is raised if any required plugins are "
"not found when running pytest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4102
msgid ""
":issue:`4375`: The ``pytest`` command now suppresses the ``BrokenPipeError`` "
"error message that is printed to stderr when the output of ``pytest`` is "
"piped and the pipe is closed by the piped-to program (common examples are "
"``less`` and ``head``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4107
msgid ""
":issue:`4391`: Improved precision of test durations measurement. "
"``CallInfo`` items now have a new ``<CallInfo>.duration`` attribute, created "
"using ``time.perf_counter()``. This attribute is used to fill the "
"``<TestReport>.duration`` attribute, which is more accurate than the "
"previous ``<CallInfo>.stop - <CallInfo>.start`` (as these are based on "
"``time.time()``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4110
msgid ""
":issue:`4675`: Rich comparison for dataclasses and `attrs`-classes is now "
"recursive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4113
msgid ""
":issue:`6285`: Exposed the `pytest.FixtureLookupError` exception which is "
"raised by `request.getfixturevalue()` (where `request` is a `FixtureRequest` "
"fixture) when a fixture with the given name cannot be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4117
msgid ""
":issue:`6433`: If an error is encountered while formatting the message in a "
"logging call, for example ``logging.warning(\"oh no!: %s: %s\", \"first\")`` "
"(a second argument is missing), pytest now propagates the error, likely "
"causing the test to fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4121
msgid ""
"Previously, such a mistake would cause an error to be printed to stderr, "
"which is not displayed by default for passing tests. This change makes the "
"mistake visible during testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4125
msgid ""
"You may suppress this behavior temporarily or permanently by setting "
"``logging.raiseExceptions = False``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4129
msgid ""
":issue:`6817`: Explicit new-lines in help texts of command-line options are "
"preserved, allowing plugins better control of the help displayed to users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4133
msgid ""
":issue:`6940`: When using the ``--duration`` option, the terminal message "
"output is now more precise about the number and duration of hidden items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4136
msgid ""
":issue:`6991`: Collected files are displayed after any reports from hooks, e."
"g. the status from ``--lf``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4139
msgid ""
":issue:`7091`: When ``fd`` capturing is used, through ``--capture=fd`` or "
"the ``capfd`` and ``capfdbinary`` fixtures, and the file descriptor (0, 1, "
"2) cannot be duplicated, FD capturing is still performed. Previously, direct "
"writes to the file descriptors would fail or be lost in this case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4145
msgid ""
":issue:`7119`: Exit with an error if the ``--basetemp`` argument is empty, "
"is the current working directory or is one of the parent directories. This "
"is done to protect against accidental data loss, as any directory passed to "
"this argument is cleared."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4149
msgid ""
":issue:`7128`: `pytest --version` now displays just the pytest version, "
"while `pytest --version --version` displays more verbose information "
"including plugins. This is more consistent with how other tools show `--"
"version`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4152
msgid ""
":issue:`7133`: :meth:`caplog.set_level() <pytest.LogCaptureFixture."
"set_level>` will now override any :confval:`log_level` set via the CLI or "
"configuration file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4155
msgid ""
":issue:`7159`: :meth:`caplog.set_level() <pytest.LogCaptureFixture."
"set_level>` and :meth:`caplog.at_level() <pytest.LogCaptureFixture."
"at_level>` no longer affect the level of logs that are shown in the "
"*Captured log report* report section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4159
msgid ""
":issue:`7348`: Improve recursive diff report for comparison asserts on "
"dataclasses / attrs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4162
msgid ""
":issue:`7385`: ``--junitxml`` now includes the exception cause in the "
"``message`` XML attribute for failures during setup and teardown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4164
msgid "Previously:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4166
msgid "<error message=\"test setup failure\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4170
msgid "Now:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4172
msgid ""
"<error message=\"failed on setup with &quot;ValueError: Some error during "
"setup&quot;\">"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4181
msgid ""
":issue:`1120`: Fix issue where directories from :fixture:`tmpdir` are not "
"removed properly when multiple instances of pytest are running in parallel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4184
msgid ""
":issue:`4583`: Prevent crashing and provide a user-friendly error when a "
"marker expression (`-m`) invoking of :func:`eval` raises any exception."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4187
msgid ""
":issue:`4677`: The path shown in the summary report for SKIPPED tests is now "
"always relative. Previously it was sometimes absolute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4190
msgid ""
":issue:`5456`: Fix a possible race condition when trying to remove lock "
"files used to control access to folders created by :fixture:`tmp_path` and :"
"fixture:`tmpdir`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4194
msgid ""
":issue:`6240`: Fixes an issue where logging during collection step caused "
"duplication of log messages to stderr."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4198 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4319
msgid ""
":issue:`6428`: Paths appearing in error messages are now correct in case the "
"current working directory has changed since the start of the session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4202
msgid ""
":issue:`6755`: Support deleting paths longer than 260 characters on windows "
