#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4373
msgid "pytest 5.4.1 (2020-03-13)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4387
msgid "pytest 5.4.0 (2020-03-12)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4392
msgid ""
":issue:`6316`: Matching of ``-k EXPRESSION`` to test names is now case-"
"insensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4395
msgid ""
":issue:`6443`: Plugins specified with ``-p`` are now loaded after internal "
"plugins, which results in their hooks being called *before* the internal "
"ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4397
msgid "This makes the ``-p`` behavior consistent with ``PYTEST_PLUGINS``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4400
msgid ":issue:`6637`: Removed the long-deprecated ``pytest_itemstart`` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4402
msgid ""
"This hook has been marked as deprecated and not been even called by pytest "
"for over 10 years now."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4405
msgid ""
":issue:`6673`: Reversed / fix meaning of \"+/-\" in error diffs.  \"-\" "
"means that something expected is missing in the result and \"+\" means that "
"there are unexpected extras in the result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4408
msgid ""
":issue:`6737`: The ``cached_result`` attribute of ``FixtureDef`` is now set "
"to ``None`` when the result is unavailable, instead of being deleted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4411
msgid ""
"If your plugin performs checks like ``hasattr(fixturedef, "
"'cached_result')``, for example in a ``pytest_fixture_post_finalizer`` hook "
"implementation, replace it with ``fixturedef.cached_result is not None``. If "
"you ``del`` the attribute, set it to ``None`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4421
msgid ""
":issue:`3238`: Option ``--no-print-logs`` is deprecated and meant to be "
"removed in a future release. If you use ``--no-print-logs``, please try out "
"``--show-capture`` and provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4424
msgid ""
"``--show-capture`` command-line option was added in ``pytest 3.5.0`` and "
"allows to specify how to display captured output when tests fail: ``no``, "
"``stdout``, ``stderr``, ``log`` or ``all`` (the default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4428
msgid ""
":issue:`571`: Deprecate the unused/broken `pytest_collect_directory` hook. "
"It was misaligned since the removal of the ``Directory`` collector in 2010 "
"and incorrect/unusable as soon as collection was split from test execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4433
msgid ":issue:`5975`: Deprecate using direct constructors for ``Nodes``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4435
msgid "Instead they are now constructed via ``Node.from_parent``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4437
msgid ""
"This transitional mechanism enables us to untangle the very intensely "
"entangled ``Node`` relationships by enforcing more controlled creation/"
"configuration patterns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4440
msgid ""
"As part of this change, session/config are already disallowed parameters and "
"as we work on the details we might need disallow a few more as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4442
msgid ""
"Subclasses are expected to use `super().from_parent` if they intend to "
"expand the creation of `Nodes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4445
msgid ""
":issue:`6779`: The ``TerminalReporter.writer`` attribute has been deprecated "
"and should no longer be used. This was inadvertently exposed as part of the "
"public API of that plugin and ties it too much with ``py.io.TerminalWriter``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4454
msgid ""
":issue:`4597`: New :ref:`--capture=tee-sys <capture-method>` option to allow "
"both live printing and capturing of test output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4457
msgid ""
":issue:`5712`: Now all arguments to ``@pytest.mark.parametrize`` need to be "
"explicitly declared in the function signature or via ``indirect``. "
"Previously it was possible to omit an argument if a fixture with the same "
"name existed, which was just an accident of implementation and was not meant "
"to be a part of the API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4461
msgid ""
":issue:`6454`: Changed default for `-r` to `fE`, which displays failures and "
"errors in the :ref:`short test summary <pytest."
"detailed_failed_tests_usage>`.  `-rN` can be used to disable it (the old "
"behavior)."
