msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4691
msgid ""
":issue:`5914`: pytester: fix :py:func:`~pytest.LineMatcher.no_fnmatch_line` "
"when used after positive matching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4694
msgid ""
":issue:`6082`: Fix line detection for doctest samples inside :py:class:"
"`python:property` docstrings, as a workaround to :issue:`python/"
"cpython#61648`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4699
msgid ""
":issue:`6254`: Fix compatibility with pytest-parallel (regression in pytest "
"5.3.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4702
msgid ""
":issue:`6255`: Clear the :py:data:`sys.last_traceback`, :py:data:`sys."
"last_type` and :py:data:`sys.last_value` attributes by deleting them instead "
"of setting them to ``None``. This better matches the behaviour of the Python "
"standard library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4709
msgid "pytest 5.3.0 (2019-11-19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4714
msgid ""
":issue:`6179`: The default value of :confval:`junit_family` option will "
"change to ``\"xunit2\"`` in pytest 6.0, given that this is the version "
"supported by default in modern tools that manipulate this type of file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4717
msgid ""
"In order to smooth the transition, pytest will issue a warning in case the "
"``--junitxml`` option is given in the command line but :confval:"
"`junit_family` is not explicitly configured in ``pytest.ini``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4720
msgid ""
"For more information, :ref:`see the docs <junit-family changed default "
"value>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4727
msgid ""
":issue:`4488`: The pytest team has created the `pytest-reportlog <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-reportlog>`__ plugin, which provides a new ``--"
"report-log=FILE`` option that writes *report logs* into a file as the test "
"session executes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4730
msgid ""
"Each line of the report log contains a self contained JSON object "
"corresponding to a testing event, such as a collection or a test result "
"report. The file is guaranteed to be flushed after writing each line, so "
"systems can read and process events in real-time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4734
msgid ""
"The plugin is meant to replace the ``--resultlog`` option, which is "
"deprecated and meant to be removed in a future release. If you use ``--"
"resultlog``, please try out ``pytest-reportlog`` and provide feedback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4739
msgid ""
":issue:`4730`: When :py:data:`sys.pycache_prefix` (Python 3.8+) is set, it "
"will be used by pytest to cache test files changed by the assertion "
"rewriting mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4741
msgid ""
"This makes it easier to benefit of cached ``.pyc`` files even on file "
"systems without permissions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4744
msgid ""
":issue:`5515`: Allow selective auto-indentation of multiline log messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4746
msgid ""
"Adds command line option ``--log-auto-indent``, config option :confval:"
"`log_auto_indent` and support for per-entry configuration of indentation "
"behavior on calls to :py:func:`python:logging.log()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4750
msgid ""
"Alters the default for auto-indention from ``\"on\"`` to ``\"off\"``. This "
"restores the older behavior that existed prior to v4.6.0. This reversion to "
"earlier behavior was done because it is better to activate new features that "
"may lead to broken tests explicitly rather than implicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4757
msgid ""
":issue:`5914`: :fixture:`testdir` learned two new functions, :py:func:"
"`~pytest.LineMatcher.no_fnmatch_line` and :py:func:`~pytest.LineMatcher."
"no_re_match_line`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4760
msgid ""
"The functions are used to ensure the captured text *does not* match the "
"given pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4763
msgid "The previous idiom was to use :py:func:`python:re.match`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4765
msgid ""
"result = testdir.runpytest()\n"
"assert re.match(pat, result.stdout.str()) is None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4770
msgid "Or the ``in`` operator:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4772
msgid ""
"result = testdir.runpytest()\n"
"assert text in result.stdout.str()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4777
msgid "But the new functions produce best output on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4780
msgid ""
":issue:`6057`: Added tolerances to complex values when printing ``pytest."
"approx``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4782
msgid ""
"For example, ``repr(pytest.approx(3+4j))`` returns ``(3+4j) ± 5e-06 ∠ "
"±180°``. This is polar notation indicating a circle around the expected "
"value, with a radius of 5e-06. For ``approx`` comparisons to return "
"``True``, the actual value should fall within this circle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4785
msgid ""
":issue:`6061`: Added the pluginmanager as an argument to "
"``pytest_addoption`` so that hooks can be invoked when setting up command "
"line options. This is useful for having one plugin communicate things to "
"another plugin, such as default values or which set of command line options "
"to add."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4795
msgid ":issue:`5061`: Use multiple colors with terminal summary statistics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4798
msgid ""
":issue:`5630`: Quitting from debuggers is now properly handled in "
"``doctest`` items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4801
msgid ":issue:`5924`: Improved verbose diff output with sequences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4803
msgid "Before:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4807
msgid ""
"E   AssertionError: assert ['version', '...version_info'] == ['version', '..."
"version', ...]\n"
"E     Right contains 3 more items, first extra item: ' '\n"
"E     Full diff:\n"
"E     - ['version', 'version_info', 'sys.version', 'sys.version_info']\n"
"E     + ['version',\n"
"E     +  'version_info',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version_info',\n"
"E     +  ' ',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version_info']"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4819
msgid "After:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4823
msgid ""
"E   AssertionError: assert ['version', '...version_info'] == ['version', '..."
"version', ...]\n"
"E     Right contains 3 more items, first extra item: ' '\n"
"E     Full diff:\n"
"E       [\n"
"E        'version',\n"
"E        'version_info',\n"
"E        'sys.version',\n"
"E        'sys.version_info',\n"
"E     +  ' ',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version',\n"
"E     +  'sys.version_info',\n"
"E       ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4837
msgid ""
":issue:`5934`: ``repr`` of ``ExceptionInfo`` objects has been improved to "
"honor the ``__repr__`` method of the underlying exception."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4839
msgid ":issue:`5936`: Display untruncated assertion message with ``-vv``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:4842
msgid ""
":issue:`5990`: Fixed plurality mismatch in test summary (e.g. display \"1 "
