#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8226
msgid ""
"Set ``xfail_strict=True`` in pytest's own test suite to catch expected "
"failures as soon as they start to pass. (:issue:`2722`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8229
msgid ""
"Fix typo in example of passing a callable to markers (in example/markers."
"rst) (:issue:`2765`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8234
msgid "pytest 3.2.2 (2017-09-06)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8239
msgid ""
"Calling the deprecated ``request.getfuncargvalue()`` now shows the source of "
"the call. (:issue:`2681`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8242
msgid ""
"Allow tests declared as ``@staticmethod`` to use fixtures. (:issue:`2699`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8244
msgid ""
"Fixed edge-case during collection: attributes which raised ``pytest.fail`` "
"when accessed would abort the entire collection. (:issue:`2707`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8247
msgid "Fix ``ReprFuncArgs`` with mixed unicode and UTF-8 args. (:issue:`2731`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8253
msgid ""
"In examples on working with custom markers, add examples demonstrating the "
"usage of ``pytest.mark.MARKER_NAME.with_args`` in comparison with ``pytest."
"mark.MARKER_NAME.__call__`` (:issue:`2604`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8257
msgid ""
"In one of the simple examples, use ``pytest_collection_modifyitems()`` to "
"skip tests based on a command-line option, allowing its sharing while "
"preventing a user error when accessing ``pytest.config`` before the argument "
"parsing. (:issue:`2653`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8266
msgid ""
"Fixed minor error in 'Good Practices/Manual Integration' code snippet. (:"
"issue:`2691`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8269
msgid "Fixed typo in goodpractices.rst. (:issue:`2721`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8271
msgid ""
"Improve user guidance regarding ``--resultlog`` deprecation. (:issue:`2739`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8275
msgid "pytest 3.2.1 (2017-08-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8280
msgid ""
"Fixed small terminal glitch when collecting a single test item. (:issue:"
"`2579`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8282
msgid ""
"Correctly consider ``/`` as the file separator to automatically mark plugin "
"files for rewrite on Windows. (:issue:`2591`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8285
msgid ""
"Properly escape test names when setting ``PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST`` environment "
"variable. (:issue:`2644`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8288
msgid ""
"Fix error on Windows and Python 3.6+ when ``sys.stdout`` has been replaced "
"with a stream-like object which does not implement the full ``io`` module "
"buffer protocol. In particular this affects ``pytest-xdist`` users on the "
"aforementioned platform. (:issue:`2666`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8297
msgid ""
"Explicitly document which pytest features work with ``unittest``. (:issue:"
"`2626`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8301
msgid "pytest 3.2.0 (2017-07-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8306
msgid ""
"``pytest.approx`` no longer supports ``>``, ``>=``, ``<`` and ``<=`` "
"operators to avoid surprising/inconsistent behavior. See the :func:`~pytest."
"approx` docs for more information. (:issue:`2003`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8310
msgid ""
"All old-style specific behavior in current classes in the pytest's API is "
"considered deprecated at this point and will be removed in a future release. "
"This affects Python 2 users only and in rare situations. (:issue:`2147`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8314
msgid ""
"A deprecation warning is now raised when using marks for parameters in "
"``pytest.mark.parametrize``. Use ``pytest.param`` to apply marks to "
"parameters instead. (:issue:`2427`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8322
msgid "Add support for numpy arrays (and dicts) to approx. (:issue:`1994`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8324
msgid ""
"Now test function objects have a ``pytestmark`` attribute containing a list "
"of marks applied directly to the test function, as opposed to marks "
"inherited from parent classes or modules. (:issue:`2516`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8328
msgid ""
"Collection ignores local virtualenvs by default; ``--collect-in-virtualenv`` "
"overrides this behavior. (:issue:`2518`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8331
msgid ""
"Allow class methods decorated as ``@staticmethod`` to be candidates for "
"collection as a test function. (Only for Python 2.7 and above. Python 2.6 "
"will still ignore static methods.) (:issue:`2528`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8335
msgid ""
"Introduce ``mark.with_args`` in order to allow passing functions/classes as "
"sole argument to marks. (:issue:`2540`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8338
msgid ""
"New ``cache_dir`` ini option: sets the directory where the contents of the "
"cache plugin are stored. Directory may be relative or absolute path: if "
"relative path, then directory is created relative to ``rootdir``, otherwise "
"it is used as is. Additionally path may contain environment variables which "
"are expanded during runtime. (:issue:`2543`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8344
msgid ""
"Introduce the ``PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST`` environment variable that is set with "
"the ``nodeid`` and stage (``setup``, ``call`` and ``teardown``) of the test "
"being currently executed. See the :ref:`documentation <pytest current test "
"env>` for more info. (:issue:`2583`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8349
msgid ""
"Introduced ``@pytest.mark.filterwarnings`` mark which allows overwriting the "
"warnings filter on a per test, class or module level. See the :ref:`docs "
"<filterwarnings>` for more information. (:issue:`2598`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8353
msgid ""
"``--last-failed`` now remembers forever when a test has failed and only "
"forgets it if it passes again. This makes it easy to fix a test suite by "
"selectively running files and fixing tests incrementally. (:issue:`2621`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8357
msgid ""
"New ``pytest_report_collectionfinish`` hook which allows plugins to add "
"messages to the terminal reporting after collection has been finished "
"successfully. (:issue:`2622`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8361
msgid ""
"Added support for :pep:`415`\\'s ``Exception.__suppress_context__``. Now if "
"a ``raise exception from None`` is caught by pytest, pytest will no longer "
"chain the context in the test report. The behavior now matches Python's "
"traceback behavior. (:issue:`2631`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8366
msgid ""
"Exceptions raised by ``pytest.fail``, ``pytest.skip`` and ``pytest.xfail`` "
"now subclass BaseException, making them harder to be caught unintentionally "
"by normal code. (:issue:`580`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8374
msgid ""
"Set ``stdin`` to a closed ``PIPE`` in ``pytester.py.Testdir.popen()`` for "
"avoid unwanted interactive ``pdb`` (:issue:`2023`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8377
msgid ""
"Add missing ``encoding`` attribute to ``sys.std*`` streams when using "
"``capsys`` capture mode. (:issue:`2375`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8380
msgid ""
"Fix terminal color changing to black on Windows if ``colorama`` is imported "
"in a ``conftest.py`` file. (:issue:`2510`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8383
msgid ""
"Fix line number when reporting summary of skipped tests. (:issue:`2548`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8385
msgid "capture: ensure that EncodedFile.name is a string. (:issue:`2555`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8387
msgid ""
"The options ``--fixtures`` and ``--fixtures-per-test`` will now keep "
"indentation within docstrings. (:issue:`2574`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8390
msgid ""
"doctests line numbers are now reported correctly, fixing `pytest-sugar#122 "
"<https://github.com/Frozenball/pytest-sugar/issues/122>`_. (:issue:`2610`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8393
msgid ""
"Fix non-determinism in order of fixture collection. Adds new dependency "
"(ordereddict) for Python 2.6. (:issue:`920`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8400
msgid "Clarify ``pytest_configure`` hook call order. (:issue:`2539`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8402
msgid ""
"Extend documentation for testing plugin code with the ``pytester`` plugin. (:"
"issue:`971`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8409
msgid ""
"Update help message for ``--strict`` to make it clear it only deals with "
"unregistered markers, not warnings. (:issue:`2444`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8412
msgid ""
"Internal code move: move code for pytest.approx/pytest.raises to own files "
"in order to cut down the size of python.py (:issue:`2489`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8415
msgid ""
"Renamed the utility function ``_pytest.compat._escape_strings`` to "
"``_ascii_escaped`` to better communicate the function's purpose. (:issue:"
"`2533`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8418
msgid ""
"Improve error message for CollectError with skip/skipif. (:issue:`2546`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8420
msgid ""
"Emit warning about ``yield`` tests being deprecated only once per generator. "
"(:issue:`2562`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8423
msgid ""
"Ensure final collected line doesn't include artifacts of previous write. (:"
"issue:`2571`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8426
msgid "Fixed all flake8 errors and warnings. (:issue:`2581`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8428
msgid ""
"Added ``fix-lint`` tox environment to run automatic pep8 fixes on the code. "
"(:issue:`2582`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8431
msgid ""
"Turn warnings into errors in pytest's own test suite in order to catch "
"regressions due to deprecations more promptly. (:issue:`2588`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8434
msgid "Show multiple issue links in CHANGELOG entries. (:issue:`2620`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8438
msgid "pytest 3.1.3 (2017-07-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8443
msgid ""
"Fix decode error in Python 2 for doctests in docstrings. (:issue:`2434`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8445
msgid ""
"Exceptions raised during teardown by finalizers are now suppressed until all "
"finalizers are called, with the initial exception reraised. (:issue:`2440`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8448
msgid ""
"Fix incorrect \"collected items\" report when specifying tests on the "
"command- line. (:issue:`2464`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8451
msgid ""
"``deprecated_call`` in context-manager form now captures deprecation "
"warnings even if the same warning has already been raised. Also, "
"``deprecated_call`` will always produce the same error message (previously "
"it would produce different messages in context-manager vs. function-call "
"mode). (:issue:`2469`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8456
msgid ""
"Fix issue where paths collected by pytest could have triple leading ``/`` "
"characters. (:issue:`2475`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8459
msgid ""
"Fix internal error when trying to detect the start of a recursive traceback. "
"(:issue:`2486`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8466
msgid ""
"Explicitly state for which hooks the calls stop after the first non-None "
"result. (:issue:`2493`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8473
msgid "Create invoke tasks for updating the vendored packages. (:issue:`2474`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8475
msgid ""
"Update copyright dates in LICENSE, README.rst and in the documentation. (:"
"issue:`2499`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8480
msgid "pytest 3.1.2 (2017-06-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8485
msgid ""
"Required options added via ``pytest_addoption`` will no longer prevent using "
"--help without passing them. (#1999)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8488
msgid "Respect ``python_files`` in assertion rewriting. (#2121)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8490
msgid ""
"Fix recursion error detection when frames in the traceback contain objects "
"that can't be compared (like ``numpy`` arrays). (#2459)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8493
msgid ""
"``UnicodeWarning`` is issued from the internal pytest warnings plugin only "
"when the message contains non-ascii unicode (Python 2 only). (#2463)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8496
msgid ""
"Added a workaround for Python 3.6 ``WindowsConsoleIO`` breaking due to "
"Pytests's ``FDCapture``. Other code using console handles might still be "
"affected by the very same issue and might require further workarounds/fixes, "
"i.e. ``colorama``. (#2467)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8505
msgid "Fix internal API links to ``pluggy`` objects. (#2331)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8507
msgid ""
"Make it clear that ``pytest.xfail`` stops test execution at the calling "
"point and improve overall flow of the ``skipping`` docs. (#810)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8512
msgid "pytest 3.1.1 (2017-05-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8517
msgid ""
"pytest warning capture no longer overrides existing warning filters. The "
"previous behaviour would override all filters and caused regressions in test "
"suites which configure warning filters to match their needs. Note that as a "
"side-effect of this is that ``DeprecationWarning`` and "
"``PendingDeprecationWarning`` are no longer shown by default. (#2430)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8523
msgid "Fix issue with non-ascii contents in doctest text files. (#2434)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8525
msgid "Fix encoding errors for unicode warnings in Python 2. (#2436)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8527
msgid ""
"``pytest.deprecated_call`` now captures ``PendingDeprecationWarning`` in "
"context manager form. (#2441)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8534
msgid "Addition of towncrier for changelog management. (#2390)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8538
msgid "3.1.0 (2017-05-22)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8542
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8544
msgid ""
"The ``pytest-warnings`` plugin has been integrated into the core and now "
"``pytest`` automatically captures and displays warnings at the end of the "
"test session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8549
msgid ""
"This feature may disrupt test suites which apply and treat warnings "
"themselves, and can be disabled in your ``pytest.ini``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8552
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = -p no:warnings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8557
msgid ""
"See the :doc:`warnings documentation page <how-to/capture-warnings>` for "
"more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8560
msgid "Thanks :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8562
msgid ""
"Added ``junit_suite_name`` ini option to specify root ``<testsuite>`` name "
"for JUnit XML reports (:issue:`533`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8564
msgid ""
"Added an ini option ``doctest_encoding`` to specify which encoding to use "
"for doctest files. Thanks :user:`wheerd` for the PR (:pr:`2101`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8567
msgid ""
"``pytest.warns`` now checks for subclass relationship rather than class "
"equality. Thanks :user:`lesteve` for the PR (:pr:`2166`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8570
msgid ""
"``pytest.raises`` now asserts that the error message matches a text or regex "
"with the ``match`` keyword argument. Thanks :user:`Kriechi` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8573
msgid ""
"``pytest.param`` can be used to declare test parameter sets with marks and "
"test ids. Thanks :user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8578
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8580
msgid ""
"remove all internal uses of pytest_namespace hooks, this is to prepare the "
"removal of preloadconfig in pytest 4.0 Thanks to :user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8584
msgid ""
"pytest now warns when a callable ids raises in a parametrized test. Thanks :"
"user:`fogo` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8586
msgid ""
"It is now possible to skip test classes from being collected by setting a "
"``__test__`` attribute to ``False`` in the class body (:issue:`2007`). "
"Thanks to :user:`syre` for the report and :user:`lwm` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8590
msgid ""
"Change junitxml.py to produce reports that comply with Junitxml schema. If "
"the same test fails with failure in call and then errors in teardown we "
"split testcase element into two, one containing the error and the other the "
"failure. (:issue:`2228`) Thanks to :user:`kkoukiou` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8595
msgid ""
"Testcase reports with a ``url`` attribute will now properly write this to "
"junitxml. Thanks :user:`fushi` for the PR (:pr:`1874`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8598
msgid ""
"Remove common items from dict comparison output when verbosity=1. Also "
"update the truncation message to make it clearer that pytest truncates all "
"assertion messages if verbosity < 2 (:issue:`1512`). Thanks :user:`mattduck` "
"for the PR"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8603
msgid ""
"``--pdbcls`` no longer implies ``--pdb``. This makes it possible to use "
"``addopts=--pdbcls=module.SomeClass`` on ``pytest.ini``. Thanks :user:"
"`davidszotten` for the PR (:pr:`1952`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8607
msgid ""
"fix :issue:`2013`: turn RecordedWarning into ``namedtuple``, to give it a "
"comprehensible repr while preventing unwarranted modification."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8610
msgid ""
"fix :issue:`2208`: ensure an iteration limit for ``_pytest.compat."
"get_real_func``. Thanks :user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the report and PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8613
msgid ""
"Hooks are now verified after collection is complete, rather than right after "
"loading installed plugins. This makes it easy to write hooks for plugins "
"which will be loaded during collection, for example using the "
"``pytest_plugins`` special variable (:issue:`1821`). Thanks :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8618
msgid ""
"Modify ``pytest_make_parametrize_id()`` hook to accept ``argname`` as an "
"additional parameter. Thanks :user:`unsignedint` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8622
msgid ""
"Add ``venv`` to the default ``norecursedirs`` setting. Thanks :user:`The-"
"Compiler` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8625
msgid ""
"``PluginManager.import_plugin`` now accepts unicode plugin names in Python "
"2. Thanks :user:`reutsharabani` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8628
msgid ""
"fix :issue:`2308`: When using both ``--lf`` and ``--ff``, only the last "
"failed tests are run. Thanks :user:`ojii` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8631
msgid ""
"Replace minor/patch level version numbers in the documentation with "
"placeholders. This significantly reduces change-noise as different "
"contributors regenerate the documentation on different platforms. Thanks :"
"user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8636
msgid ""
"fix :issue:`2391`: consider pytest_plugins on all plugin modules Thanks :"
"user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8643
msgid ""
"Fix ``AttributeError`` on ``sys.stdout.buffer`` / ``sys.stderr.buffer`` "
"while using ``capsys`` fixture in python 3. (:issue:`1407`). Thanks to :user:"
"`asottile`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8647
msgid ""
"Change capture.py's ``DontReadFromInput`` class to throw ``io."
"UnsupportedOperation`` errors rather than ValueErrors in the ``fileno`` "
"method (:issue:`2276`). Thanks :user:`metasyn` and :user:`vlad-dragos` for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8651
msgid ""
"Fix exception formatting while importing modules when the exception message "
"contains non-ascii characters (:issue:`2336`). Thanks :user:`fabioz` for the "
"report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8655
msgid ""
"Added documentation related to issue (:issue:`1937`) Thanks :user:"
"`skylarjhdownes` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8658
msgid ""
"Allow collecting files with any file extension as Python modules (:issue:"
"`2369`). Thanks :user:`Kodiologist` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8661
msgid ""
"Show the correct error message when collect \"parametrize\" func with wrong "
"args (:issue:`2383`). Thanks :user:`The-Compiler` for the report and :user:"
"`robin0371` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8666
msgid "3.0.7 (2017-03-14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8669
msgid ""
"Fix issue in assertion rewriting breaking due to modules silently discarding "
"other modules when importing fails Notably, importing the ``anydbm`` module "
"is fixed. (:issue:`2248`). Thanks :user:`pfhayes` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8674
msgid ""
"junitxml: Fix problematic case where system-out tag occurred twice per "
"testcase element in the XML report. Thanks :user:`kkoukiou` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8677
msgid ""
"Fix regression, pytest now skips unittest correctly if run with ``--pdb`` (:"
"issue:`2137`). Thanks to :user:`gst` for the report and :user:`mbyt` for the "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8680
msgid ""
"Ignore exceptions raised from descriptors (e.g. properties) during Python "
"test collection (:issue:`2234`). Thanks to :user:`bluetech`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8683
msgid ""
"``--override-ini`` now correctly overrides some fundamental options like "
"``python_files`` (:issue:`2238`). Thanks :user:`sirex` for the report and :"
"user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8686
msgid ""
"Replace ``raise StopIteration`` usages in the code by simple ``returns`` to "
"finish generators, in accordance to :pep:`479` (:issue:`2160`). Thanks to :"
"user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8689
msgid ""
"Fix internal errors when an unprintable ``AssertionError`` is raised inside "
"a test. Thanks :user:`omerhadari` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8692
msgid ""
"Skipping plugin now also works with test items generated by custom "
"collectors (:issue:`2231`). Thanks to :user:`vidartf`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8695
msgid ""
"Fix trailing whitespace in console output if no .ini file presented (:issue:"
"`2281`). Thanks :user:`fbjorn` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8697
msgid ""
"Conditionless ``xfail`` markers no longer rely on the underlying test item "
"being an instance of ``PyobjMixin``, and can therefore apply to tests not "
"collected by the built-in python test collector. Thanks :user:`barneygale` "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8704
msgid "3.0.6 (2017-01-22)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8706
msgid ""
"pytest no longer generates ``PendingDeprecationWarning`` from its own "
"operations, which was introduced by mistake in version ``3.0.5`` (:issue:"
"`2118`). Thanks to :user:`nicoddemus` for the report and :user:"
"`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8710
msgid ""
"pytest no longer recognizes coroutine functions as yield tests (:issue:"
"`2129`). Thanks to :user:`malinoff` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8713
msgid ""
"Plugins loaded by the ``PYTEST_PLUGINS`` environment variable are now "
"automatically considered for assertion rewriting (:issue:`2185`). Thanks :"
"user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8717
msgid ""
"Improve error message when pytest.warns fails (:issue:`2150`). The type(s) "
"of the expected warnings and the list of caught warnings is added to the "
"error message. Thanks :user:`lesteve` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8721
msgid ""
"Fix ``pytester`` internal plugin to work correctly with latest versions of "
"``zope.interface`` (:issue:`1989`). Thanks :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8724
msgid ""
"Assert statements of the ``pytester`` plugin again benefit from assertion "
"rewriting (:issue:`1920`). Thanks :user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the report "
"and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8727
msgid ""
"Specifying tests with colons like ``test_foo.py::test_bar`` for tests in "
"subdirectories with ini configuration files now uses the correct ini file (:"
"issue:`2148`).  Thanks :user:`pelme`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8731
msgid ""
"Fail ``testdir.runpytest().assert_outcomes()`` explicitly if the pytest "
"terminal output it relies on is missing. Thanks to :user:`eli-b` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8736
msgid "3.0.5 (2016-12-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8738
msgid ""
"Add warning when not passing ``option=value`` correctly to ``-o/--override-"
"ini`` (:issue:`2105`). Also improved the help documentation. Thanks to :user:"
"`mbukatov` for the report and :user:`lwm` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8742
msgid ""
"Now ``--confcutdir`` and ``--junit-xml`` are properly validated if they are "
"directories and filenames, respectively (:issue:`2089` and :issue:`2078`). "
"Thanks to :user:`lwm` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8745
msgid ""
"Add hint to error message hinting possible missing ``__init__.py`` (:issue:"
"`478`). Thanks :user:`DuncanBetts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8747
msgid ""
"More accurately describe when fixture finalization occurs in documentation (:"
"issue:`687`). Thanks :user:`DuncanBetts`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8749
msgid ""
"Provide ``:ref:`` targets for ``recwarn.rst`` so we can use intersphinx "
"referencing. Thanks to :user:`dupuy` for the report and :user:`lwm` for the "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8752
msgid ""
"In Python 2, use a simple ``+-`` ASCII string in the string representation "
"of ``pytest.approx`` (for example ``\"4 +- 4.0e-06\"``) because it is "
"brittle to handle that in different contexts and representations internally "
"in pytest which can result in bugs such as :issue:`2111`. In Python 3, the "
"representation still uses ``±`` (for example ``4 ± 4.0e-06``). Thanks :user:"
"`kerrick-lyft` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8757
msgid ""
"Using ``item.Function``, ``item.Module``, etc., is now issuing deprecation "
"warnings, prefer ``pytest.Function``, ``pytest.Module``, etc., instead (:"
"issue:`2034`). Thanks :user:`nmundar` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8761
msgid ""
"Fix error message using ``approx`` with complex numbers (:issue:`2082`). "
"Thanks :user:`adler-j` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8764
msgid ""
"Fixed false-positives warnings from assertion rewrite hook for modules "
"imported more than once by the ``pytest_plugins`` mechanism. Thanks :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8768
msgid ""
"Remove an internal cache which could cause hooks from ``conftest.py`` files "
"in sub-directories to be called in other directories incorrectly (:issue:"
"`2016`). Thanks :user:`d-b-w` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8772
msgid ""
"Remove internal code meant to support earlier Python 3 versions that "
"produced the side effect of leaving ``None`` in ``sys.modules`` when "
"expressions were evaluated by pytest (for example passing a condition as a "
"string to ``pytest.mark.skipif``)(:issue:`2103`). Thanks :user:`jaraco` for "
"the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8777
msgid ""
"Cope gracefully with a .pyc file with no matching .py file (:issue:`2038`). "
"Thanks :user:`nedbat`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8782
msgid "3.0.4 (2016-11-09)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8784
msgid ""
"Import errors when collecting test modules now display the full traceback (:"
"issue:`1976`). Thanks :user:`cwitty` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8787
msgid ""
"Fix confusing command-line help message for custom options with two or more "
"``metavar`` properties (:issue:`2004`). Thanks :user:`okulynyak` and :user:"
"`davehunt` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8790
msgid ""
"When loading plugins, import errors which contain non-ascii messages are now "
"properly handled in Python 2 (:issue:`1998`). Thanks :user:`nicoddemus` for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8793
msgid ""
"Fixed cyclic reference when ``pytest.raises`` is used in context-manager "
"form (:issue:`1965`). Also as a result of this fix, ``sys.exc_info()`` is "
"left empty in both context-manager and function call usages. Previously, "
"``sys.exc_info`` would contain the exception caught by the context manager, "
"even when the expected exception occurred. Thanks :user:`MSeifert04` for the "
"report and the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8799
msgid ""
"Fixed false-positives warnings from assertion rewrite hook for modules that "
"were rewritten but were later marked explicitly by ``pytest."
"register_assert_rewrite`` or implicitly as a plugin (:issue:`2005`). Thanks :"
"user:`RonnyPfannschmidt` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8804
msgid ""
"Report teardown output on test failure (:issue:`442`). Thanks :user:"
"`matclab` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8807
msgid ""
"Fix teardown error message in generated xUnit XML. Thanks :user:`gdyuldin` "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8810
msgid ""
"Properly handle exceptions in ``multiprocessing`` tasks (:issue:`1984`). "
"Thanks :user:`adborden` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8813
msgid ""
"Clean up unittest TestCase objects after tests are complete (:issue:`1649`). "
"Thanks :user:`d-b-w` for the report and PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8818
msgid "3.0.3 (2016-09-28)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8820
msgid ""
"The ``ids`` argument to ``parametrize`` again accepts ``unicode`` strings in "
"Python 2 (:issue:`1905`). Thanks :user:`philpep` for the report and :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8824
msgid ""
"Assertions are now being rewritten for plugins in development mode (``pip "
"install -e``) (:issue:`1934`). Thanks :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8828
msgid ""
"Fix pkg_resources import error in Jython projects (:issue:`1853`). Thanks :"
"user:`raquelalegre` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8831
msgid ""
"Got rid of ``AttributeError: 'Module' object has no attribute '_obj'`` "
"exception in Python 3 (:issue:`1944`). Thanks :user:`axil` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8835
msgid ""
"Explain a bad scope value passed to ``@fixture`` declarations or a "
"``MetaFunc.parametrize()`` call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8838
msgid ""
"This version includes ``pluggy-0.4.0``, which correctly handles "
"``VersionConflict`` errors in plugins (:issue:`704`). Thanks :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8844
msgid "3.0.2 (2016-09-01)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8846
msgid ""
"Improve error message when passing non-string ids to ``pytest.mark."
"parametrize`` (:issue:`1857`). Thanks :user:`okken` for the report and :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8849
msgid ""
"Add ``buffer`` attribute to stdin stub class ``pytest.capture."
"DontReadFromInput`` Thanks :user:`joguSD` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8852
msgid ""
"Fix ``UnicodeEncodeError`` when string comparison with unicode has failed. (:"
"issue:`1864`) Thanks :user:`AiOO` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8855
msgid ""
"``pytest_plugins`` is now handled correctly if defined as a string (as "
"opposed as a sequence of strings) when modules are considered for assertion "
"rewriting. Due to this bug, much more modules were being rewritten than "
"necessary if a test suite uses ``pytest_plugins`` to load internal plugins (:"
"issue:`1888`). Thanks :user:`jaraco` for the report and :user:`nicoddemus` "
"for the PR (:pr:`1891`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8861
msgid ""
"Do not call tearDown and cleanups when running tests from ``unittest."
"TestCase`` subclasses with ``--pdb`` enabled. This allows proper post mortem "
"debugging for all applications which have significant logic in their "
"tearDown machinery (:issue:`1890`). Thanks :user:`mbyt` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8867
msgid ""
"Fix use of deprecated ``getfuncargvalue`` method in the internal doctest "
"plugin. Thanks :user:`ViviCoder` for the report (:issue:`1898`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8872
msgid "3.0.1 (2016-08-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8874
msgid ""
"Fix regression when ``importorskip`` is used at module level (:issue:"
"`1822`). Thanks :user:`jaraco` and :user:`The-Compiler` for the report and :"
"user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8877
msgid ""
"Fix parametrization scope when session fixtures are used in conjunction with "
"normal parameters in the same call (:issue:`1832`). Thanks :user:`The-"
"Compiler` for the report, :user:`Kingdread` and :user:`nicoddemus` for the "
"PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8881
msgid ""
"Fix internal error when parametrizing tests or fixtures using an empty "
"``ids`` argument (:issue:`1849`). Thanks :user:`OPpuolitaival` for the "
"report and :user:`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8884
msgid ""
"Fix loader error when running ``pytest`` embedded in a zipfile. Thanks :user:"
"`mbachry` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8891
msgid "3.0.0 (2016-08-18)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8893
msgid "**Incompatible changes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8896
msgid ""
"A number of incompatible changes were made in this release, with the intent "
"of removing features deprecated for a long time or change existing behaviors "
"in order to make them less surprising/more useful."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8899
msgid ""
"Reinterpretation mode has now been removed.  Only plain and rewrite mode are "
"available, consequently the ``--assert=reinterp`` option is no longer "
"available.  This also means files imported from plugins or ``conftest.py`` "
"will not benefit from improved assertions by default, you should use "
"``pytest.register_assert_rewrite()`` to explicitly turn on assertion "
"rewriting for those files.  Thanks :user:`flub` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8907
msgid "The following deprecated commandline options were removed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8909
msgid "``--genscript``: no longer supported;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8910
msgid "``--no-assert``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8911
msgid "``--nomagic``: use ``--assert=plain`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8912
msgid "``--report``: use ``-r`` instead;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8914
msgid "Thanks to :user:`RedBeardCode` for the PR (:pr:`1664`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8916
msgid ""
"ImportErrors in plugins now are a fatal error instead of issuing a pytest "
"warning (:issue:`1479`). Thanks to :user:`The-Compiler` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8919
msgid "Removed support code for Python 3 versions < 3.3 (:pr:`1627`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8921
msgid ""
"Removed all ``py.test-X*`` entry points. The versioned, suffixed entry "
"points were never documented and a leftover from a pre-virtualenv era. These "
"entry points also created broken entry points in wheels, so removing them "
"also removes a source of confusion for users (:issue:`1632`). Thanks :user:"
"`obestwalter` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8927
msgid ""
"``pytest.skip()`` now raises an error when used to decorate a test function, "
"as opposed to its original intent (to imperatively skip a test inside a test "
"function). Previously this usage would cause the entire module to be skipped "
"(:issue:`607`). Thanks :user:`omarkohl` for the complete PR (:pr:`1519`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8932
msgid ""
"Exit tests if a collection error occurs. A poll indicated most users will "
"hit CTRL-C anyway as soon as they see collection errors, so pytest might as "
"well make that the default behavior (:issue:`1421`). A ``--continue-on-"
"collection-errors`` option has been added to restore the previous behaviour. "
"Thanks :user:`olegpidsadnyi` and :user:`omarkohl` for the complete PR (:pr:"
"`1628`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8937
msgid ""
"Renamed the pytest ``pdb`` module (plugin) into ``debugging`` to avoid "
"clashes with the builtin ``pdb`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8939
msgid ""
"Raise a helpful failure message when requesting a parametrized fixture at "
"runtime, e.g. with ``request.getfixturevalue``. Previously these parameters "
"were simply never defined, so a fixture decorated like ``@pytest."
"fixture(params=[0, 1, 2])`` only ran once (:pr:`460`). Thanks to :user:"
"`nikratio` for the bug report, :user:`RedBeardCode` and :user:`tomviner` for "
"the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8945
msgid ""
"``_pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch`` class has been renamed to ``_pytest."
"monkeypatch.MonkeyPatch`` so it doesn't conflict with the ``monkeypatch`` "
"fixture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8948
msgid ""
"``--exitfirst / -x`` can now be overridden by a following ``--maxfail=N`` "
"and is just a synonym for ``--maxfail=1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8952 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9274
msgid "**New Features**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8954
msgid ""
"Support nose-style ``__test__`` attribute on methods of classes, including "
"unittest-style Classes. If set to ``False``, the test will not be collected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8958
msgid ""
"New ``doctest_namespace`` fixture for injecting names into the namespace in "
"which doctests run. Thanks :user:`milliams` for the complete PR (:pr:`1428`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8962
msgid ""
"New ``--doctest-report`` option available to change the output format of "
"diffs when running (failing) doctests (implements :issue:`1749`). Thanks :"
"user:`hartym` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8966
msgid ""
"New ``name`` argument to ``pytest.fixture`` decorator which allows a custom "
"name for a fixture (to solve the funcarg-shadowing-fixture problem). Thanks :"
"user:`novas0x2a` for the complete PR (:pr:`1444`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8970
msgid ""
"New ``approx()`` function for easily comparing floating-point numbers in "
"tests. Thanks :user:`kalekundert` for the complete PR (:pr:`1441`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8974
msgid ""
"Ability to add global properties in the final xunit output file by accessing "
"the internal ``junitxml`` plugin (experimental). Thanks :user:`tareqalayan` "
"for the complete PR :pr:`1454`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8978
msgid ""
"New ``ExceptionInfo.match()`` method to match a regular expression on the "
"string representation of an exception (:issue:`372`). Thanks :user:"
"`omarkohl` for the complete PR (:pr:`1502`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8982
msgid ""
"``__tracebackhide__`` can now also be set to a callable which then can "
"decide whether to filter the traceback based on the ``ExceptionInfo`` object "
"passed to it. Thanks :user:`The-Compiler` for the complete PR (:pr:`1526`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8986
msgid ""
"New ``pytest_make_parametrize_id(config, val)`` hook which can be used by "
"plugins to provide friendly strings for custom types. Thanks :user:`palaviv` "
"for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8990
msgid ""
"``capsys`` and ``capfd`` now have a ``disabled()`` context-manager method, "
"which can be used to temporarily disable capture within a test. Thanks :user:"
"`nicoddemus` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8994
msgid ""
"New cli flag ``--fixtures-per-test``: shows which fixtures are being used "
"for each selected test item. Features doc strings of fixtures by default. "
"Can also show where fixtures are defined if combined with ``-v``. Thanks :"
"user:`hackebrot` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:8999
msgid ""
"Introduce ``pytest`` command as recommended entry point. Note that ``py."
"test`` still works and is not scheduled for removal. Closes proposal :issue:"
"`1629`. Thanks :user:`obestwalter` and :user:`davehunt` for the complete PR "
"(:pr:`1633`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9004
msgid "New cli flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9006
msgid ""
"``--setup-plan``: performs normal collection and reports the potential setup "
"and teardown and does not execute any fixtures and tests;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9008
msgid ""
"``--setup-only``: performs normal collection, executes setup and teardown of "
"fixtures and reports them;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9010
msgid ""
"``--setup-show``: performs normal test execution and additionally shows "
"setup and teardown of fixtures;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9012
msgid ""
"``--keep-duplicates``: py.test now ignores duplicated paths given in the "
"command line. To retain the previous behavior where the same test could be "
"run multiple times by specifying it in the command-line multiple times, pass "
"the ``--keep-duplicates`` argument (:issue:`1609`);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9017
msgid ""
"Thanks :user:`d6e`, :user:`kvas-it`, :user:`sallner`, :user:`ioggstream` "
"and :user:`omarkohl` for the PRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9019
msgid ""
"New CLI flag ``--override-ini``/``-o``: overrides values from the ini file. "
"For example: ``\"-o xfail_strict=True\"``'. Thanks :user:`blueyed` and :user:"
"`fengxx` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9023
msgid "New hooks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9025
msgid "``pytest_fixture_setup(fixturedef, request)``: executes fixture setup;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9026
msgid ""
"``pytest_fixture_post_finalizer(fixturedef)``: called after the fixture's "
"finalizer and has access to the fixture's result cache."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9029
msgid "Thanks :user:`d6e`, :user:`sallner`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9031
msgid ""
"Issue warnings for asserts whose test is a tuple literal. Such asserts will "
"never fail because tuples are always truthy and are usually a mistake (see :"
"issue:`1562`). Thanks :user:`kvas-it`, for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9035
msgid ""
"Allow passing a custom debugger class (e.g. ``--pdbcls=IPython.core.debugger:"
"Pdb``). Thanks to :user:`anntzer` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9039 ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9305
msgid "**Changes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9041
msgid ""
"Plugins now benefit from assertion rewriting.  Thanks :user:`sober7`, :user:"
"`nicoddemus` and :user:`flub` for the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9044
msgid ""
"Change ``report.outcome`` for ``xpassed`` tests to ``\"passed\"`` in non-"
"strict mode and ``\"failed\"`` in strict mode. Thanks to :user:`hackebrot` "
"for the PR (:pr:`1795`) and :user:`gprasad84` for report (:issue:`1546`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/changelog.rst:9048
msgid ""
"Tests marked with ``xfail(strict=False)`` (the default) now appear in "
"JUnitXML reports as passing tests instead of skipped. Thanks to :user:"
